text:
Nothing special. I ordered take out (chicken teriyaki dinner) and my order was ready very promptly. However, when I got home my chicken was not cut up--it was just served in huge chunks. There was not enough sauce and the chicken itself seemed bland.

The saving grace is the California roll, which is very good. The imitation crab meat is quite tasty because it's not too sweet. Avocado is fresh as well.

Price is average for Santa Barbara (~$10-15/plate). Not sure I'll be back.

text: Writing a review again after having my last mysteriously deleted... i was calling out this Salon like it was. The owner Debbie is rude and disrespectful, like the common thug. This Salon should be renamed Salon B for Butchery, just looks like a slaughter house. Very plain white walls and DRY WALL DUST coating the edges of the floor, Very unlike the photos shown on yelp. I deleted this app because i started receiving hate messages for my scathing and honest review. Was even reached out by the store owner Debbie. Instead of trying to make my experience better or trying to make an angry customer happy, i was bombarded with choice words and serious child like attitude from all types of people including Debbie. Very un-lady like very unprofessional. NOT WORTH YOUR TIME, super high prices and super long wait times as well just to have your hair "butchered".

text: I'm sad and angry to say that my father didn't have the flowers delivered to his funeral mass until too late.  Imagine how annoyed I was that the Lily's representative was not very concerned.  He came up with three different reasons why they were late and not one of them was acceptable.  I let him know that he should somehow compensate us for the fact that the flowers were not there.  After much back and forth, he said he could give me store credit.  Store credit???  I would never use them again to get the store credit.  I don't normally do reviews, however, if you need flowers for something as life changing as a funeral, save yourself the additional grief and use a more reputable, reliable, and caring company.

text:
This place is solid. The food is pretty good. Props for being open 24 hours and having refried beans as an option for beans to put in your burrito.

If you've never been here before, think Chipotle. But a dollar or two more expensive, better tortillas, and more authentic Mexican ingredients. The assembly line thing is the same.

The nachos my friend got that I sampled were pretty epic as well. 

No complaints, just a little pricey for my taste. That explains the 3. But definitely a place to hit up when in the Isla Vista area. Especially at 4 in the morning.

name: Santa Barbara School of Mosaic Art
categories: Education, Specialty Schools
text: I bought a groupon as a gift for myself to try something new. I attended the beginner's class this last weekend. I think I expected a more "class-like" environment and was happily surprised that the educational part was short, but very thorough, and we were encouraged to delve right in to our projects. All the necessary tools, tiles, samples, protective gear, and other materials were organized beautifully. The class was held outdoors in a covered patio area and the atmosphere was Santa Barbara casual and cool. There was lots of hands on learning, great suggestions, appropriate praise and some beautiful art was created in just 2 days! Tami, the instructor, was very down to earth and made sure she was available for each student but never "hovered", which would have made me uncomfortable. A wonderful, wonderful experience!

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True'}
categories: Home & Garden, Shopping, Home Decor, Home Services, Interior Design, Furniture Stores, Mattresses
text:
The trundle bed in our small guest bedroom took up too much space so we decided to replace it with a wall bed. We found a wide selection of wallbeds  at the Comfort Zone Sleep Gallery located at 5708 Hollister Avenue in Goleta.  The salesperson, Manuela, was extremely helpful and thorough. We ordered a wall bed and mattress for our guest bedroom. We got such good service that we ordered a replacement mattress for our master bedroom. 

The wallbed was custom manufactured and both the wallbed and mattresses were delivered and the old mattress was removed free of charge within just a few weeks of purchase.

The wallbed was expertly installed in just a couple of hours. We paid a little more and got a high quality wall bed with custom overhead lighting.

We love both the wallbed and the new mattresses . . .and we highly commend the company for their service.

text:
Came here on a slower night. It has been on our list of places to try and we walk by all the time. Here was our experience. 

The atmosphere, service was very friendly they are clearly doing the best they can with what they've got. Not all of the propane heaters were on and some of them didn't work and other tables ended up moving a couple times around us. 

The food, we were told before ordering "it's family style so probably order one to two entrees per person" which seems counterintuitive to the phrase family style but maybe that's just me. Additionally the entrees are minimum about $18 which seems very expensive for needing two per person. We got the eggplant dish which was essentially a medium sized bowl of jimmy dean hot ground sausage over white rice with large sliced and slightly grilled in oil eggplant pieces... for $18... by no means was it bad in fact it is something I would probably make at home. That is the problem though, there was nothing interesting or special about and it is cheap ingredient food being charged at a fine dining price. 

With all this though, the food wasn't terrible, the service was friendly, why 3 stars? Well because at the end of feeling a little ripped off by a significantly overpriced cheap meal I get the bill to see that every check automatically includes a 20% gratuity. Now it's not that I didn't want to tip my server, it's the fact that they decided to basically just tac on 20% with little to no warning and some cheap excuse on the bottom of the receipt, it feels more like the owner of this restaurant is just money hungry. The margin on a small $18 bowl of white rice has to be huge.

name: Tree Surfers
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True'}
categories: Tree Services, Home Services
text: Damian and crew did a truly wonderful job in transforming several  50 foot Hollywood junipers on either side of our front yard. These junipers were planted decades ago, well before we bought our home, and they'd become overgrown, shedding like crazy on not just our yard, but also on both our neighbors' property. We love our neighbors and when one of them pointed out recently the mess that was dropping on their lawn from our trees, I called around for estimates. Damian came by and took the time to give me detailed recommendations on how to prune back without harming the junipers. Long story short-they went from looking like shaggy, hulking monstrosities to absolutely stunning Monterey Pine-like beauties. While not cheap (tree work never is, especially with licensed pros like Damian) his price was more than competitive. And now-I think the house and yard got a boost in curb appeal! Thanks Damian!

text:
Pretty average for a bowling alley. Generic. Not bad by any means, but that's before you see the arcade. I might be unique in having the mindset that bowling alleys are only as good as their arcade. Just about every bowling alley you go to is going to operate the same way, and it's all about the same level of fun when you do the actual bowling. But when you're sick of striking or gutter-balling, don't you want a new experience to supplement the frustration from either yourself or your friends? That's what a bowling alley arcade is for. Balance. 

You guys need a newer, bigger arcade!

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
categories: Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt, Food, Desserts
text:
Let me start by saying this: THIS IS THE BEST ICE CREAM SHOP IN SANTA BARBARA.

I've been here many times in the past and never have I been disappointed. Flavor availability changes depending on the season, but there are the standard regular popular flavors to be had as well. 

Location/Parking: On the corner of De La Vina and Mission Street with one way streets. Parking is extremely tight here and the only thing I don't like about this location. Probably only a total of about 5 parking spots with the rest street parking. You want to test your parallel parking skills? Here's your chance.

Flavors: What can I say? Take you pick and choose before you get in line if it's short. If you get behind an indecive group or a long line, you'll have time to pick. Or maybe not. The list is LONG for flavors. No joke. And they do ice cream sandwiches too. Feeling stunned yet? I know I was on my first visit. I got the cookies n' cream in a cup and I was in heaven. I could dive into that ice cream bucket if it were big enough.

Summary: I could care less if it's cold out, I will come here for my ice cream when I'm in the mood. There are other locations in CA (Santa Monica and Los Angeles), but the experience just isn't the same for some reason and the parking isn't easy either for the other ones. If you visit Santa Barbara, you must try this place if you're in the mood for ice cream. I think these guys would give  Ben&Jerry a run for their money if they ever decide to go the oddball-flavor route

text:
Came here for lunch on a Sunday with some friends. Gets pretty busy, so order quickly indoors and enjoy outdoor seating overlooking the harbor, and they will bring out your order. 

I ordered #41 Salmon Teriyaki Bento Box (Lunch Special) for $10.95. The teriyaki salmon and tempura (shrimp and veggies) was pretty good. My friend really enjoyed her chicken teriyaki bowl. The quality of sushi is neither poor or amazing. Nothing really fancy. The service was quick and the view was nice. Great for a quick bite.

So yes, the rooms are tight. You are snug as a bug in a rug here but boy that location ! We're beach people so close proximity to sandy paradise always attracts our attention. 
We used to visit Santa Barbara quite regularly and when Covid struck, there was a tug pulling us to return. 
SB is just so relaxing.

The room is small but comfy. The pool was shut on our visit but the new renovations feel great. 

We had a sliver of a beach view but it was lovely. 

I can imagine this beach haven will be a blast in summer. Give them a try!

Just got married here.  There were no lines and in fact they accepted us a few minutes earlier than our appointment.  Our officiant was Gabe.  He was very professional and was such a help to us.  He was even able to provide us with official copies of the marriage cert THAT DAY! 

The grounds are beautiful and we took ample photos inside and out.  Be sure to be out of there by 4:30-5 p.m.  The custodial staff was YELLING at us to leave.  We were in too good of a mood to let them get us down.  We just sent our guests across the street to the French Table for a break with appetizers and drinks.

This is a wonderful spot.  Very warm and inviting with eclectic, fun furnishings.
We sat in front and then explored the patio after eating.  It could use some
"warming up"...perhaps more plants or some tiny lights in the huge fig tree out there.
Small lights on the tables?  The food was perfect and reasonably priced.  One could
easily make a dinner out of two or three of their small plates.  We had the lamb
chops and the tamale corn cakes with three sauces.  Both delicious.  There is
ample parking at the public lot so that too is convenient. Will definitely visit again.

name: Ross Dress for Less
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True'}
categories: Women's Clothing, Men's Clothing, Shopping, Discount Store, Home Decor, Department Stores, Fashion, Home & Garden
text:
Ross Dress for Less lives up to it's name. If you are looking for stylish clothing, I wouldn't recommend Ross, although once in a while you can find a hidden treasure. However, Ross is a fantastic place if you're looking for affordable kitchenware, dog beds/toys, wallets, decorative pillows, and a great assortment of throws, typically for around $19.99. If you're living on a budget, Ross is a good option. At this particular location in five points, there is a loss prevention staff member named Steffany, who has helped me on more than one occasion with questions and is extremely friendly and helpful, and is a great individual to be greeted by and see as you are leaving. Unfortunately, a majority of the other staff could use some customer service training.
I also believe additional cashiers during busy hours would improve the shopping experience greatly as lines can get frustratingly long.
The furniture section is not large but has some good finds that look pretty standard and hold up well for a reasonable, perhaps slightly below average, cost.
I rate this establishment at this location 3 stars because it provides what is advertised (lower costs), has a decent variety of options, but the quality of clothing is a bit cheap and the staff are generally pretty unapproachable (will not offer help unless asked, even if you accentuate the classic "very lost" look, and are often chatting with other staff ignoring the customer's needs)

name: Inn by the Harbor
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Hotels, Hotels & Travel, Event Planning & Services
text: After reading reviews and seeing the pictures we decided the Inn looked like a decent place to stay. When we arrived the front was nice but it is located on a very busy, windy road next to the freeway. The gentleman at the front desk was very nice and he quickly checked us in. This is where it went downhill. They don't show you one side of the building because it shares a driveway with an apartment building next door. It basically looks like a large alley. Our "Deluxe" room was in the back and as soon as we entered we could smell mustiness throughout. We also saw right away that it looked nothing like the pictures of the rooms online. Bare white walls with mismatched, furniture and carpeting. The TV was smaller than my desktop computer's and the Lazy Boy looked like something from a garage sale. The curtains were open on the sliding glass window and there were a couple of housekeeping carts parked against it as the storage room was right there as well. The kitchen was original, old cabinets with doors that didn't close and the original hood. Old tile counter and floors with blemishes. The fridge had yellow stains all over the front. The bathroom was the most renovated part of the room but they still didn't change out the shower head or the neck of it (rusty). And when they put in a new mirror they decided to go with a tiny one when a larger one would have been so much more useful. The room really looked nothing like the pictures they advertised with. For $350/night we expected to get at least what they showed online. It seems like there are some rooms that are renovated but I guess it's the luck of the draw for that and also for which side of the building you're on. Anyway, be warned that their pics don't match what really is there. Disappointed to say the least.

name: Haven Barber & Shop

name: Cathedral Oaks Athletic Club
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Trainers, Fitness & Instruction, Gyms, Tennis, Active Life
text: I have been training in local gyms for over 35 years. I've seen it all. From the tiny one room weight room at the YMCA, to the laughably over-managed and under-improved Spectrum(now the Bay Club), the old adage, "You get what you pay for," is always the mantra. However, with Cathedral Oaks Athletic Club, you get so much more. From the management to the staff, from the two pools to the outstanding food at the cafe, I would NEVER go anywhere else to train. Yes, the club is not brand new, but it is very clear to me that the management works hard everyday to bring you the best possible experience in a multidimensional athletic facility. To those who complain about a pool temperature of less than 80 degrees, and more shade on the outdoor lounging areas, I say: Go somewhere else because you have no idea how good you really have it at Cathedral Oaks Athletic Club!

text: I was in Santa Barbara shopping on a beautiful day and I thought this place looked like a great spot for people watching.  I was seated outside right along State St. Ordered a few drinks from the happy hour menu. 2 for the price of one...not bad at all.   I did have to ask for chips and salsa which I thought was kind of odd. I ordered a carnitas chimichunga with beans and rice on the side. We did not wait long for our food. The food was good and very reasonably priced. The refried beans and rice were very tasty. Maybe the best beans I have had at a restaurant. Overall I really enjoyed this place especially the location. The only reason I did not give it another star was the service. The young staff did not seem too eager to help out anyone with anything.  Good servers know how to go out of the way to help someone, the crew they had that day should not be in the service industry.

categories: Restaurants, Music Venues, American (New), Arts & Entertainment, Nightlife, Seafood, Steakhouses
text: I guess I'll give it two stars. Could be one based on price. The food was not very good, the interior of the place is just ok. Their signature dish is Killer Shrimp. The bartender told us it was "to die for." Hardly. Really just not very good. Some people here are commenting about the fact that it's "very spicy" but only if you are kind of a wimp on spice. I found it really to be flavorless. It's shrimp in a bowl of broth with too much butter. I also got a bowl of New England clam chowder. Mediocre. Both Brophy's and the place at the end of the pier in SB have much, much better chowder. In fact, both are excellent. SB is a terrible food town in general so maybe this place can survive because so bad restaurants do in the town. I give it 6-12 months.

The selection of goods in this store is pretty awesome! Loads of great brands and super fun selections for the kiddos. 

It will be nice to shop there when I have a little more time.

I came here once before and got the bahn mi sandwich and a thai tea which were good but nothing that would have made me need to come back to try other dishes. 
Well, I came back again after a friend suggested we eat here. Trying to be on the healthier side, I decided to order the fried rice salad. To me, it sounded like something I'd randomly put together at the house when I need to get rid of leftovers, but then I was caught off guard when it came out looking super healthy with bean sprouts and sunflower seeds on top. I was a little nervous because I didn't want to go THAT healthy. LOL. Fortunately, I started eating the salad and discovered a wonderful mix of fresh greens, herbs, peppers and tomatoes, along with perfectly cooked riced. There was a good amount of flavor in every bite. I would definitely go there again for this dish and am curious to see what else they have to offer that may surprise me.

categories: Nightlife, Restaurants, Steakhouses, Bars, American (Traditional)
text:
To be fair- we went on a Sunday night right after a huge graduation weekend, when they were slammed, and ran out of several items. Tha place looks great- seat 270 in 3 sections, plus a long bar. Aviation theme with hanging model airplanes throughout (they are very close to the airport).
Anyhow, Sunday night, Father's Day, went with my family @8:30, there are about 3 other parties, and a couple at the bar, but other than that- it's dead. No music, and when we asked if they ever play music (hint)- she said yeah, this is usually the classic rock area, country is over there and reggae on the patio, but we're really tired... So for atmosphere on that night, they get zero stars. Now for the food- we ordered a bunch of appetizers and drinks- pulled pork sliders were gross- no flavor, wet, like they'd been in a slow cooker, no smoke, buns both over toasted, and soggy from the pork. One bite. The bacon wrapped jalapeño poppers were fresh and huge, but the peppers were almost uncooked and crunchy. The potato skins were decent, but the skins weren't very crisp- and when you put hot crisp on top of wet lettuce, they get soggy. We quickly got them off the lettuce and finished them all. The deep fried zucchini also had to be saved from the wet lettuce, and was the best of the appetizers.The buffalo wings had an extra gooey sauce, so they were really messy, the chicken wasn't cooked long enough- (or the oil in the fryer wasn't hot enough), the skin was rubbery, the meat was close to undercooked, but the sauce was all heat, and only heat, and goo.  So for the food, they barely get 1 star.
Now the service is why I write this. I know you had a tough weekend and you're tired and you want to go home, but you're open and it's Father's Day, and you could try to make us feel like we were welcome, instead you made us feel like you wanted us out of there as fast as possible so you could close early and leave. So for service you get minus stars.
The one star is mostly for the beer- Fig Mountain IPA.

text: This is bar none the BEST ice cream I have ever had! They put some love into this artisan ice cream! My uncle franchised a Baskin Robbins aka 31 flavors when I was a kid and scooping ice cream was my first job. I love ice cream and I truly appreciate great ice cream. This beats the socks off 31. They are organic, sourcing Strauss Family Milk. All flavors are incredible. I found out about RORIS Ice Cream because I now have a pizza catering business and we set up next to there kitchen ! ....and when they make the mint chip the mint smell infuses the air. Oh my gosh!   So amazing! The mint chip is outstanding! So minty fresh and chocolately chip! But my favorite is the coconut chocolate! It's dairy free! (You would never guess) Make with coconut milk and Belgian chocolate! It's named Romans Chocolate Coconut after their son!  The lemon curd is so delicious too and root beer float! Get out! So stoked to have some delicious ice cream here in Santa Barbara! Can't wait for my next fix!

name: Hotel Milo Santa Barbara
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'DogsAllowed': 'True'}
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text:
This has been one of the worst experiences I have ever had at a Hotel.  I'm not one who takes reviews seriously when deciding on a hotel to stay and you out there may not also, but believe me, the Hotel Oceana SB is horrendous with piss poor customer service!

Their front desk agents are not knowledgeable about the location and lack common sense.  I had gotten a massage with my gf at their spa, and told them not to charge any charges to our room and we would rather pay on the spot, which we did.  Surprise, Surprise, upon check out we were charged double.  The agent corrected the mistake and finally checked us out; I thought everything was ok.  

Before our long trip back to the bay area, I had stopped for gas, finding that my card was declined.  For some odd reason, the competent front desk agent charged my card over $10K resulting in an overdraft in my operating account when we just stayed for two nights at a standard room.  

Having complained, this took 5 weeks to resolve which resulted in further  mistakes by the hotel and resulted in further charges totaling $20K.  This matter also went all the way up to the CFO of Hotel Oceana Corporate, but regardless the situation took 5 weeks which is clearly ridiculous.

We were given a complimentary stay not too long ago for a deluxe remodel ocean view room.  I had arranged flowers to be set up prior to our arrival as a surprise which I had coordinated w/ their director of rooms.  By promise, he guaranteed the flowers would be there upon our arrival and even offered to have a bottle of red wine waiting.  As we checked in flowers were not there and as we walked to our room, we saw a bell boy running to our room with a wine bottle and glasses.  

I was expecting to meet the director of rooms during our stay, but he was too busy with operational matters.  After check-in we did not receive a warm call (as a normal hotel would typically do) to make sure that a VIP guest has no issues with the room.  

Moreover, the room was missing one of those "no house keeping" placards which I had requested the front desk to drop off and to not have house keeping come in and clean.  Low and behold we did not receive a placard until check out and house keeping attempted to come in on several occasions.  

During our stay I bumped into the Guest Services Manager, who checked me in and was aware of my entire situation, and I never received a greeting, nor did he remember my face. Upon check out I told him how disappointed I was with everything and that I was hoping to meet the director of rooms. He was apologetic and promised that the director email me.  Until this day, no email.    

Although this trip was on the house, their service is just ridiculous, and until they revamp their management team, this hotel will never be successful in the long run. 

The Hotel is pretty nice considering how they are fixing all the rooms, and the location is very convenient to State street and across the beach, but this hotel has some very incompetent people who should NOT be working in the hospitality business!

text:
They've got a bit of NOSTALGIA goin' on, up in here!  Technology has certainly altered the way we watch movies, sometimes incredibly so. But there is just something cool about lounging in the car/van & watching a flick in the open skies with family and friends!  Drive-in movies are not an easy find, and yet, here is West Wind Santa Barbara Drive-In Theater, in all its splendor!  It's the closest drive-in screen to Ventura County.  This blast from the past is actually located in Goleta, so it's about 40 minutes from my hometown.  Yelp directions are on point.  Snack bar has tasty options and popcorn hasn't been overly salty.  Still doesn't have something you want?  No prob!  Bring it!  I transport my own spicy ramen pipin' hot and Calbee Shrimp Flavored Chips to munch on.  YUUP!!!  I slurp & crunch away like nobody's business AND I'm not bothering a soul!  Need to stretch the appendages a lil bit?  Please, feel free to roam.  How about pre-movie distractions like gettin' thrown popcorn at me by my kids to make in my mouth?!?  Oh yeah, fun times!  No way we'd get away with that @ any walk in cinema!  But, it's all good here!  Some details to know...

*Prices: $7.25 adults; $1 kids 5-11y/o; under 5y/o FREE!  These prices are usually for a double feature, too!
*Try to get there 30 minutes early.  There is only 1 cashier & as it gets closer to start time, the longer it takes to get in.  
*Smaller cars park in front section, while SUVs & vans are relegated the the middle & back areas.  Mobile homes are in the WAAAY back!  It's basically a dirt lot, slightly uneven, so no fancy shoes.  Its beach California, so there is the normal little chill in the air at night.
*All digital projection, all digital sound.  Tune in to 96.9 FM on your vehicle's stereo.  Staff is more than ready to help with a jump start, just in case your vehicle is having too good a time!

West Wind does the drive-in experience just fine at a great price.  My fams loves the freedom to talk & move... well, I love it.  My young squires don't know they prefer it, but they aren't bothering others, that's for sure.  Staff is friendly and helpful.  There's never been a glitch with the movie projection.  As this is THE ONLY Drive-in for miles & miles, its as good as it's going to get around here.

categories: Home & Garden, Home Services, Kitchen & Bath, Appliances, Shopping, Nurseries & Gardening, Building Supplies, Hardware Stores
text:
I received excellent customer service on the floor.  My 2-star​ response is due to the check out procedure.  Currently,​ we are in the ​ "Safer at Home" mode for California due to Covid19.  I waited in line outside The Home Depot standing on the red tape to keep my social distance from those around me.  During check out all that was available was self check out.  Once again I waited in line standing on the marked tape to keep my social distance.  Upon checking out one of the employees was being very impatient with a customer who was having trouble with the self check out the ​handheld ​scanner.   When it was my turn to purchase my items I did not want to pick up the scanner. I asked the employee who was wearing gloves to scan my items for me.  She spoke to me as if I was a child  " P I C K  U P  T H E  S C A N N E R" I told her I was not going to pick up the scanner after other customers had used it and since she had gloves could she please scan my items for me.  I was met with a "huff and a "puff". Why would I want to touch a handheld​ scanner after 100​ people had touched it that day?!  Come on Home Depot! You should have employees scanning items for people and helping with the touch screen.
I tried to find a place online to message the manager about this situation but was unable to find any contact email or phone so I posted on Yelp

categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Food, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Bars, Seafood, Restaurants, Wine Bars, Cocktail Bars, American (New), Nightlife
text:
We hadn't had a meal all day, and were at this particular mall, so we decided to trust yelp and give this place a try. It was around 5:15 pm and it turns out that it was happy hour until 6 pm, but only if you head to the chaotic left side of the restaurant, where it's self seating. Also, good luck finding a seat.

With that said, after a while of walking in circles, we finally spotted a corner table, next to some greenery and had to ask for the table to be cleaned. While we were waiting for that, the next two tables cleared up. Our table could seat 4, the middle table could seat 2, and the table after that could seat 4 as well. We were standing there when the waiter that would be serving us asked us if we could move to the middle table, which was getting hit by the sun, so that an older (not elderly, just a white couple in their early 60s)couple could sit there. Both tables were getting hit by the sun, ours probably 10% less than theirs. We weren't sure why they wanted to sit us elsewhere, especially when it's a self seating situation, so that someone else could have it, with no reason given. Had they told us it was for a medical reason, maybe it would have made more sense, however, we weren't entirely too pleased to have had hunted down a table by ourselves, only to be asked to move so someone else could have it for no reason at all, other than because they wanted that particular table.

Anyway, we ordered 8 clams, chef's choice, a happy hour order of the calamari, some bread, and then off the regular menu. I ordered shrimp with two sides. The shrimp was a good size, with not a lot of flavoring or spices, accompanied by plain melted butter, a rather flavorless parmesan potato pancake, and roasted veggies that tasted really citrusy. My fiance ordered the lobster ravioli, which was really tasty and was accompanied by two sides of garlic bread. 

We didn't get refills unless we flagged someone down, which was pretty bad. The total bill was $71 and some change. The fish was fresh, but the service was lacking due to the number of patrons in the restaurant.

categories: Tuscan, Seafood, Wine Bars, Restaurants, Bars, Nightlife, Italian
text:
On the way home to the Bay Area from LA, boyfriend and I decided to take 101 home for the more scenic drive, compared to highway 5. We wanted to stop for dinner on the way home, and Santa Barbara seemed like a good choice since both of us haven't really been there before.

So OF COURSE, I hopped onto Yelp via my Blackberry, and searched for Italian restaurants cause I wanted some pasta. Found a couple of restaurants with good reviews, but Ca' Dario had both that and a lower price range than other restaurants.

When we got to Ca' Dario, it was pretty empty (it was still kinda early, around 5:15pm). We figured the restaurant would remain slow since it was Super Bowl day, but we were wrong. By 6:30pm, the restaurant was quite busy and packed. (we noticed this because at first, my bf joked that the restaurant seemed over staffed). Anyhow, I knew it must be a good restaurant if it was getting packed on a Sunday, let alone Super Bowl Sunday. 

Moving on... the food at Ca' Dario was awesome. Service however, was a bit spotty. One of the servers was really friendly, even though she wasn't our server. The other staff members just acted somewhat aloof. 

BF ordered the Free Range Chicken, which was one of the specials of the day. It came with potatoes, beets, and spinach on the side. The chicken looked delicious, and tasted delicious. Very soft, juicy, and tender chicken meat, which this yummy glazed sauce on top. The sides were also very good. BF loved it.

I ordered the thin spaghetti with clams - YUH UH MEE! The clams were very tasty and not chewy at all. The pasta was in a light, clam/wine broth sauce. I really liked that the sauce was so light, and that they left a good amount of it in, so the pasta was setting in a little amount of soup, pretty much. It was good because I could spoon the soup like sauce up, and drench each bite of clam and pasta with it.

Overall, great restaurant. Food was delish, and it was a great stop to our trip home.

name: ella & louie flowers
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'BusinessParking': 'None', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'None', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'"}
categories: Flowers & Gifts, Florists, Shopping, Event Planning & Services, Floral Designers
text: I was recommended Ella & Louie through a friend and I absolutely loved the flowers that Tracey did for my wedding. I had a chuppah on the beach and asked for a small amount of flowers to decorate it. She did the most amazing job on it, there were loads of flowers and the beauty of it added so much to the scene, it felt so dreamy. She also made beautiful bouquets, boutonnieres and table arrangements that went perfectly with the relaxed, natural look of the wedding. I don't really know much about flowers and Tracey came up with some great suggestions for me. She's lovely to deal with and the price is totally reasonable. I never thought flowers would be an aspect of my wedding that I would love so much, but they looked amazing and make the day and photos so special. Thank you Tracey.

text: We've gone to this restaurant for years and the bar is fun, the food and service is usually good, but this last time I went to there on a Saturday night in December with my family of five. I could not believe how noise it was in there. The food and service are decent, but the noise level makes it so you cannot hear the person next to you or anyone across the table. All you want to do is get the heck out of there :-(   I would not recommend going here for any holiday celebration. There are too many great restaurants to have to subject yourself and your company to this. I think well go back to Cadiz where I know it's all good.

text:
Orders about sixty dollars worth of food. Ordered chicken nachos..no chicken came on the nachos.

Ordered one meal to go when we arrived. Fifty minutes later..they realized they never made it.

Should be noted: I've ordered chicken fajitas to go three times. All three times I got home to realize they didn't give me tortillas.

I've even talked to management in the past. I was polite and asked why then made so many mistakes. He didn't have an answer.

Sadly..I will not return here. This place has messed my order up four out of the last four times I've been here. Like George W. Said "fool me a bunch of times, shame on me."

name: Westbury Lawrence W DDS
categories: Oral Surgeons, Health & Medical, Dentists, Periodontists
text: Dr. Westbury has been an excellent periodontist for me. I had gum surgery last week to repair a receding gum around a canine. The surgery was over in less than an hour, pain minimal, and Dr. Westbury has wonderful "bedside manners" and followup. Today I get some sutures out and again a very positive experience. I heartily recommend Dr. Westbury.

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{u'divey': False, u'hipster': False, u'casual': True, u'touristy': None, u'trendy': False, u'intimate': False, u'romantic': False, u'classy': False, u'upscale': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': False, u'brunch': False, u'lunch': True, u'dinner': True, u'latenight': None, u'dessert': False}"}
categories: Salad, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Pizza
text:
This pizza place is AWESOME! There is a self-serve salad station for those of you who like to customize your food. The best part though, is definitely their pizzas! My friends and I had a hankering for pizza, so this was the closest location to our hotel. They had a great variety of combinations and all of their pizza was freshly-made in their wood-based ovens. We were able to watch our pizza being made, from beginning to end. 

The employees there were cheerful and energetic and made waiting a breeze for us. The medium pizza with 3 toppings cost us around $16-$18. I think that if you don't mind the quality/freshness of your pizza and just want pizza in general, then maybe go with a cheaper place (Little Caesar's). But Rusty's pizza dough is so delicious and light - the pizza was also piping hot and fresh out of the oven! Worth every penny!

text:
This my friends, is a phenomenal restaurant. The appetizers were all incredibly flavorful. 

I'm not a fan of mushrooms but the champinones... it's like they were foraged from heaven. Sooo good! 

Bravo on the patatas bravas as well. 

The chorizo y pollo paella takes the cake though. Each bite had so much texture and packed such a pow. Order it. You won't regret it.

The drinks were also pretty great. The Costa Blanca was crisp and refreshing- a great treat.

categories: Steakhouses, Bars, Brewpubs, Breweries, American (Traditional), Nightlife, Sports Bars, Restaurants, Food, Burgers, Comfort Food, Seafood
text:
Went there over the weekend while visiting the 'rents again. Last time I went was over 5 years but I remember it being really good. I wasn't that hungry but the Brewhouse Enchiladas with filet mignon caught my eye and I am so glad it did. It was more like a "pastel azteca" (AKA mexican lasagna) but way better than my version. First of all it had filet mignon with mushrooms and it was covered with their sauce. The flavors together were sooooooo good that I finish my plate. The corn pancake was really good because it soak up the left over sauce. 
The hubby ordered the gorgonzola salad which was my 2nd choice. I LOVE gorgonzola and the salad had enough to not over power it but still to enjoy it.  
It was a little loud so I do not recommend it for an intimate meal with your spouse/partner. But I will definetely go again with the hubby to enjoy a good meal and drinks!

name: Trattoria Vittoria
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'full_bar'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'HappyHour': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'None', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': None, 'divey': False, 'intimate': None, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': None, 'casual': None}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': None, u'street': True, u'lot': False, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': False, u'brunch': False, u'lunch': None, u'dinner': True, u'latenight': False, u'dessert': None}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True'}
categories: Italian, Restaurants
text:
This is my favorite Italian restaurant in Santa Barbara. And that is saying something, because there are other very good options in town. 

We dined at Trattoria Vittoria last night, celebrating my birthday, and everyone in my family agreed it might even be our favorite restaurant in town, period. The burrata is excellent, with thinly shaved prosciutto and wonderful vinegar. The ravioli with pink sauce is spectacular (and is our go-two favorite). One of my sons ordered the veal tortellini last night, and we all agreed it was definitely worth ordering again... I had the halibut special and loved it. 

Bonus if you get Shayne as your server. He's funny, friendly, and attentive without being smothering. He's also very knowledgeable about the menu and the wine list. 

LOVE this place!!!

name: Julienne
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': True, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'"}
categories: Restaurants, American (New), Seafood, French
text:
Ambiance/Service:
Julienne was good but failed to really wow me.  The atmosphere is great.  It's intimate setting is great for a romantic night out but allows for a certain level of quaint comfort as well.  Service was excellent, the wait staff was friendly, knowledgeable and even called a cab for us at the end of our meal!  I must say, however that I would not pay as much as they charge for the food that we had.  Not to say that the food was bad by any means, it simply just did not merit the exotic red Ferrari price tag.  

Food:
For a stater we had the pork and shitaake mushroom crepe with truffles.  This was probably the highlight of the meal for me.  The sauce was light and creamy but not overbearing.  The pork was seasoned nicely and the mushrooms added a nice compliment.  For the entree I had the crisped pork belly with mushroom risotto.  The pork belly was delectable and cooked to perfection but the risotto that accompanied it was a sore disappointment.  The dish as a whole was under seasoned and bland.  My gf had the braised lamb cheeks with cubed potatoes and spinach.  This dish was too salty and over seasoned.  The flavor was good and the meat again was cooked nicely but the seasoning was way off.  I would have ordered dessert but the selection was sparse and I was disappointed with the rest of my meal.  Overall, the food was slightly above average.  Good, but not spectacular.  

Wrap-up:
Given the price, I would not return.  They charge elite prices for slightly above average food.  To be fair, what Julienne lacks in spectacular food, it makes up for an excellent service and great ambiance.  Perhaps the seasoning mishaps may have been an isolated occasion, but I would not return.

text:
Hands-down, my favorite Italian food in Santa Barbara... a truly intimate setting with handcrafted, authentically Italian dishes. Go with small parties only, and time to waste. There's a wide variety of local wines, served mostly by the bottle. The portions are medium to small, but packed with flavor and will leave you completely satisfied. The pumpkin sage ravioli is insane, as is the entire gelato bar. 

Also, a great option if you're looking to have a small dinner catered. Call ahead!

name: The Ritz-Carlton Bacara, Santa Barbara
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '4', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False'}
categories: Restaurants, Beauty & Spas, American (New), Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Massage, Resorts, Day Spas, Hotels & Travel, Venues & Event Spaces
text:
What a beautiful hotel! The grounds are amazing and serene. This was our first time visiting this hotel and love it. The room was lovely with a great partial view of the ocean and a cute trail. We had a balcony that was pretty big!  It was raining part of our stay but either way it was nice. Valet was attentive and quick every time. Staff wore masks every day. 

Now to the downside of our experience here. The room although beautiful smelled dirty. It had a smell of mildew or wet dog. Not sure how often the carpet is cleaned but the smell was annoying. 

We came here to celebrate our daughters 21st birthday. We were given a room with one king bed. Sadly for us, we were told that that was all they had and a rollaway would be a good option. That was fine at the end of the day and didn't make a fuss since we didn't want to ruin our daughters weekend. 

Then yesterday I went to buy my daughter a cake and flowers. Mind you our room was at a distance so I went to wait for my ride. I asked a gentlemen to have someone take me. He said no problem! Then I'm waiting a few minutes and a couple came behind me. Well the ride guy came, skipped me and went straight to them and asked if he could assist them and gave them a ride to their car. Seriously!!!!!???! I had been waiting , my back was hurting and my bags were heavy. I was furious. This is unacceptable! Walking was not an option for me since it was far, it's downhill, and floor was wet and yes I was in pain! 

I complained to another person who came by and he said he'd talk to him but I was so upset and in pain I wanted to cry. This gentlemen was quick to take me to my room which I appreciated. 

I'll speak to the manager when I depart from here. I would have gladly given this place 4 stars but 3 stars is best for now.

name: Lavender Inn by the Sea
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text: Recently while transitioning our daughter to SBCC, I searched for an affordable hotel and came across The Lavender Inn by the Sea.  Although this is a motel style property, every detail was lovely.  The rooms are very traditionally decorated, but immaculate. Our room came with complimentary wifi, a bottle of champagne, complimentary bottled water daily, continental breakfast which included an assortment of pastries, cereals, yogurts, juices, coffee and tea.  Every afternoon, the motel offers complimentary milk and cookies, and in the early evening, wine and cheese.  The grounds are meticulously kept with beautiful vines and trellis' throughout, giving it a beautiful ambiance. There is also a swimming pool and hot tub. The room rates are beyond reasonable for the Santa Barbara area and the motel is just three blocks from the Santa Barbara Pier.  The motel also offers complimentary bicycles.  The Lavender Inn by the Sea was simply a great find and we will stay there again!

text:
I had read a lot of "The Mill" during it's development and decided to come check it out now that it's open. Originally, my plan was to hit up the brewery but soon realized it wasn't open for business yet. My girlfriend and I -- never to waste a trip -- wandered into Potek instead and sampled the wine. 

She opted for simply a glass of Riesling while I did the tasting flight. The Grenache and Syrah were both very good. My girlfriend enjoyed the dry Riesling but I think the Blanc de Blanc sparkling wine was her most favorite. The server described it as being very dry and "yeasty" which is a perfect adjective. It's vaguely reminiscent of a beer in that it has that bread flavor to it. Very interesting and definitely tasty. 

The space is great and the server was very nice and knowledgable about the wines. We'd definitely come back here for the casual wine tasting or even to purchase a glass and sit outside in the courtyard.

name: The Engine Company
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Automotive, Auto Repair, Auto Parts & Supplies, Oil Change Stations, Transmission Repair
text:
I really tried to like Peter and give him a fair shake but he really deserves many of the negative reviews that he has received. Call me genuinely is a shyster. He is untrustworthy.  He will often and perform repairs without telling you how much it will cost and then when you show up, he will ask for some ridiculous amount of money. 
The real issue is his attitude. He is very condescending and argumentive.  And far too often he doesn't end up fixing the problem correctly the first time.  He cops out by saying, "You told me to fix this part but that's not what's wrong".  
In the simplest terms, you'll most likely regret going to him.

name: Santa Barbara Amtrak Station
categories: Trains, Public Transportation, Transportation, Hotels & Travel
text: Train ride home was cancelled had to take first train home the next morning. Between hotel, cab fare, missed wages and purchasing additional tickets was over $500 out of pocket. We were in the cafe car the air was broken as well as the restroom. Imagine being stuck in a hot overflowing portapotty for 5 hours. It an awful way to end a beautiful anniversary weekend.  Ticket checkers were not friendly or apologetic for the situation. The first one scolded us for having only 2 people at a table and said we may be asked to move if a family wants it as it requires a party of 3, he acted like he didn't smell the stench and acted surprised the bathroom was broken. Got to Union station and they acted like they fixed it. A supervisor got on watching the guys working and at the top of his lungs shoutingJESUS CHRIST IT STINKS WHAT IS GOING ON HERE. WHY DOES IT STINK SO BAD? WHY IS IT SO HOT IN HERE? THERE IS NO AIR! After they pretended to fix it, The First Lady who used the bathroom came out and told the lady waiting in line that it wouldn't flush so she might want to use a different bathroom. Yay us... We got to smell poop the rest of the way home. The ticket checker who got on at Union station also started to scold us that we were not supposed to sit at group table and I interrupted that the bathroom was broken and she said that they weren't supposed to unlock it, of course it doesn't work the air is broken in this car. She proceeds to lock it without putting an out of order sign on it. We  wrote out of order on a cup and put it on the handle as people would wait thinking that someone was occupying it. I had high hopes that Amtrak would be better. My husband now calls Amtrak the Poop train. A normal business would not survive a day with this kind of service from the crappy attitudes to the horrific environment you are trapped in just to get home. If I were you I would seriously weigh your savings vs. plane or driving a car, because Amtrak litterally stinks. I will update with my request for reimbursement. Ps the only reason I included cost of cab is because we had family to pick us up on Sunday but they were at work on Monday

There can be a bit of a wait on the weekends but it's worth it!

text: Just got back from a five day trip to Santa Barbara and out of those five days, we found and ate at Cuernavaca three days.  They were that good.  Loved their al pastor tacos, tried their quesadilla, burrito and taco de chicharon, even brought some home.  Also loved their taco de raja con queso.  I understand they have one in Ventura and opening in Oxnard.  Would most definitely make the drive.  Would highly recommend this place to anyone visiting SB.

text: Only reason I ran into this place was because it was the only place while looking thru Yelp as a good rated place to eat. So I decided to give it a shot. Being morning time and being a fan of Chorizo and bagels, seen that they had a chorizo/egg breakfast bagel. Was really impressed with the right amount of chorizo added since most places you taste more egg than chorizo. This place just made my morning, being the food explorer that I am.. this place left me wanting to try more and I sure want to try the rest of the menu. Now I have more of a reason to come to Santa Barbara.. this place and a cupcake spot on State St.

name: Tammy Dobrotin - State Farm Insurance Agent
attributes: {'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False'}
categories: Financial Services, Home & Rental Insurance, Life Insurance, Financial Advising, Auto Insurance, Insurance
text: DO NOT USE STATE FARM INSURANCE,I REPEAT DO NOT USE STATE FARM INSURANCE!!!! I only gave them 1 star so I can leave a review they don't even deserve that star. I'm very frustrated, upset and unsatisfied with STATE FARM INSURANCE. I've been with them an have my life insurance (which I thought was great) & my automobile insurance since November 2016'. They over charged me by 60$ then said they would credit me last month- never did. So I had to call tell them to credit me, they still didn't credit me & said they would call me back- never did again. Now all of a sudden my car insurance is 228$ every month from 180$ a month. 1st off they lied by saying they would credit me. 2nd of all they were rude an said I was not a priority to them. 3rd of all I had to call them n track them down for them to tell me that they "kinda" credited me & now everyone's premium went up & they've been too busy to call me back. I'm soo upset & inconvenienced by them because now I have no flippin car or life insurance!!! This is soo rude & unprofessional!!! Who tells someone who is a paying customer that they are not a priority to them!!!??? I Live in Santa Barbara and everything is already expensive af.

text: I was looking for a nice winery to do a tasting while here in the west coast visiting and yelpers once again did not disappoint . It's a little hard to find this place when navigating in the area for the first time and you gotta find street parking. It's a cute little room with bar seating and a lounge area. We were the only ones there as it had just opened. I did the Chardonnay tasting for $15 and it was wonderful . The rose was my favorite with the estate Chardonnay coming in second . They have a bubbly tasting as well that was $20 but since I was the only one doing the tasting I'm going to have to reserve that for next time . Chardonnay is my fave white wine and I must say this place knows what they're doing !

categories: Restaurants, Delis, Coffee & Tea, Breakfast & Brunch, Food, Gluten-Free, Cafes, Beer, Wine & Spirits
text: For lunch, this is my absolute favorite place to go for a healthy, high-quality, light meal. The salad bar is the best I've ever experienced, and allows me to have a light, protein-rich lunch that keeps me feeling energetic through the rest of my work day rather than sinking into a post-lunch coma after a big sandwich or the like. The house-made poppyseed vinaigrette is one of my favorite dressings at any restaurant in Santa Barbara and is now sold by the bottle in their refrigerated section. There is also a lovely selection of drinks from natural cola to kombucha, as well as an array of gluten-free and sugar-free baked goods (and full-gluten and sugar as well!). It is a gift to have this establishment in Santa Barbara.

name: Cielo Spa Boutique
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'AcceptsInsurance': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Skin Care, Beauty & Spas, Hair Removal, Day Spas, Massage, Waxing
text:
Both my girlfriend and I were BLOWN AWAY! The massage I got was by far the best (see below for the details). My girlfriend also thinks it was one of the best massages she's ever had. She gets massages a lot (at least several times a months) and she's picky!

I got a 60 minute Swedish massage from Brenda. Both of her hands and lower arms were synchronized so that each stroke felt amazing! Also, her pressure was just perfect; it was as if she knew exactly what I wanted. As soon as she started massaging me, all I could think about was how soon I could come back to Santa Barbara to get another massage from her. My girlfriend got a 60 minute deep tissue massage with Emily. Obviously, she was thinking about the same thing. As soon as our massages were over, she said "we should have got 90 minutes!" We left the spa extremely happy and relaxed with a lingering dreamy feeling.

Booking was easy too. We did this at the last minute; so, we called them. We exchanged a couple of texts and they found Emily and Brenda for us. Quick and painless!

I cannot think of anything other than 5 stars for Cielo Spa! 

NOTES
The word "spa" used here can be a bit misleading for some people. They offer "spa treatments" like facials and waxing but they do not have a steam room, etc. If you're thinking of changing into a bathrobe in a locker room, soaking in a hot tub, lounging in the lounge before getting a massage, this is not your place. I just do not want anyone to be disappointed. If you're just looking for amazing massages, I highly recommend that you try Cielo Spa Boutique!

******************************
If you found something useful in my review, please hit "useful" so that I can improve my reviews. If you love food and traveling, follow me, or better yet, let's be friends on Yelp! Thank you and happy Yelping!

name: Segway of Santa Barbara
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False'}
categories: Arts & Entertainment, Scooter Rentals, Bike Rentals, Hotels & Travel, Active Life, Local Services, Scooter Tours, Tours
text:
OK, never ever been on a Segway before in my life...until today!
Gotta admit, there is a huge nerd factor to riding one...admit it, you've laughed at people on these things.. And it's probably because you've never been on one..HOWEVER...once you do, they are a total blast to ride!

If ever in Santa Barbara, this is the tour to take. Unfortunately, I totally suck at remembering names, but the tour guides we had we're super cool. Especially the leader. Great knowledge of Santa Barbara, knew all the hot spots in town for anything and everything, even stopped and had a cupcake..which was awesome! 

This is one of those things that I will make a point to come back and do again. Was a blast! Saw parts of town and interesting sites you'd probably never get to on your own. I really can't recommend it enough. And don't worry, after 5 minutes on a segway it's EZ!

4 stars for the view; really nice to be there on the ocean.
Service is okay...
had the Ciopino and still wonder why there is a full crab claw in there that (if you want to eat it) has to be cracked!! Imagine, all your seafood is in a nice tomatoeish broth and you are going to put your hands in the dish to crack that claw?! Come on...IF you are on a date, do not get this...

PARKING difficult as it is a beach spot for tons of people, including locals.

name: White & Grube Orthodontist
attributes: {'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'AcceptsInsurance': 'True'}
categories: Orthodontists, Dentists, Health & Medical
text:
So glad I chose White and Grube!

Getting braces in college can be complicated, but I really wanted to get my teeth fixed. The staff provides excellent service. Appointments were very easy. I bused from Goleta to Santa Barbara every six weeks to see Dr. White, and every time was a breeze. They have free toothbrushes, tea, and coffee. 

The price is a bit high, but it's Santa Barbara, and I got what I paid for. I know people who went to do braces in the Bay Area and got delayed by over a year. For me, I felt Dr. White focused his full attention to my needs whenever I visited, and he tracked my progress strictly. 

From my consultation to the very end of my progress, Dr. White was super accommodating. My estimate for my braces was 15 months, and we took them off right at 15 months! Getting them off felt amazing. Dr. White knew that for my schedule, I wanted to take them off a bit earlier than anticipated because of school and traveling. While my bottom row of teeth have barely a misalignment, I am so satisfied with my look.

categories: Desserts, Food, Gluten-Free, Burgers, Restaurants, Italian
text: Worst meal I've ever had.  To start off, the table we were sat at had a smell of sewage/rotten eggs. We shouldve left then. I ordered the macademia encrusted halibut salad which per the description was supposed to include tomatoes, avocado, green onion, fresh tangerine and roasted almond tossed with rice vinegar and olive oil. What I got was a plate of romaine lettuce, what looked like the mini oranges out of a can,  a handful of slivered almonds and the toughest, flavorless and smallest piece of "halibut" I've ever eaten in my life. Im not sure how an italian restaurant runs out of tomatoes, but clearly all the salad makings were missing that night. Our waitress was sweet and I didnt have the heart to tell her how awful my food was when she came by to ask how things were, but I think she sensed we were disappointed because she didnt come back until we were ready for the bill. The other items that were ordered were the steak dinner special and chicken picatta. Both were just okay at best. We will not be returning.

text:
We stopped here for a quick bite to eat on a Saturday night.
We ordered:
Teriyaki steak dinner with Caesar side salad and sticky white rice. The steak was difficult to cut and was very tough. The rice was mushy and was the equivalent to minute rice. The Caesar dressing was like a ranch and tarter sauce mixed together and was actually good. 
Teriyaki chicken k-bob with white sticky rice and veggies and pineapple. The chicken was dry and tasteless, barely any veggies that were extremely dried out... Almost burnt. The rice was the same as above. The only thing good was the Martinelli's apple juice and the dressing.
The family next to us wasn't very impressed as the three kids and dad didn't finish their food and actually ended up splitting fries.

categories: Latin American, Restaurants, Mexican, New Mexican Cuisine
text:
Santo Mezcal's Happy Hour is absolutely wonderful!  Not only are the food and drink prices very reasonable but service was good as well.  Some places that serve Happy Hour have small food portion sizes, but Santo Mezcal is NOT one of those places... My husband I both had the crab quesadilla and shared the nachos.  The quesadilla was stuffed with fresh crab and the nachos were very delicious-- fully loaded with melted cheese, beans, pico de gallo, quacamole.  The 3 salsas served with the chips are also excellent... I liked the smokey chipotle one the best.   Also loved the red Sangria-- so refreshing (and strong, too!)!

The patio overlooks State St. and they are dog friendly.  They bring out the heaters when the wind picks up.

We will definitely be returning for Happy Hour when we visit Santa Barbara again!

name: San Roque Pet Hospital
categories: Pet Services, Veterinarians, Pets, Pet Sitting
text:
January 12, 2022
We were long-time clients of Goleta Airport Pet Hospital/ San Roque Pet Hospital (from mid-2012 to beginning-2022).

San  Roque Pet Hospital used to be wonderful, now...it has changed to a practice that feels like it Nickle and dimes clients for services rendered and provides inconsistent, empathetic care.  

About the front office staff:  
The reception has been inconsistently helpful and warm; the latter being that we felt rushed and left as though we were more of a bother or annoyance for calling.


About Dr. Peterson:  
She may have 15+ years of experience as a DVM, and she may have done a superb job in caring for countless animals, but she did not impart that level of expertise to us via clear and concise communication related to the care and management of our dog who was newly diagnosed with diabetes.  We were often given sub-par instructions and education....mostly being referred to YouTube videos for clarification rather than hearing it from her...and so our follow-up questions and concerns might have felt overwhelming, but that's what resulted from the limited and incomplete information we received from her.  

Additionally, she did not impart a reassuring attitude when discussing our dog's care, and so we were often left feeling uneasy and a lack of confidence in our ability to properly manage his symptoms, and even a lack of confidence in the process of managing his symptoms.  

We would have appreciated a warm smiling and the time taken to ask if we understood the game plan...her bedside manner left us wanting to switch practitioners.  However, we do appreciate her time and effort. 

 ----Please, San Roque Pet Hospital, make sure your DVMs have the time to properly spend with each Client so that we can see the best of who they are and what they do.  We know she is probably a lot better than what we experienced from her.----


About the office flow:  
The current system of communicating through a front office staff member to your Tech and then ultimately the Tech to the Vet has led to delays in communication and maybe even instructions that are lost in translation.  My husband was very upset about the instructions we received by the office about bringing in a stool sample.  He followed office instructions only to find out on the day of our appointment that the stool sample was too old to run for accurate testing results, and yet we literally paid for this error in instructions that was given to us by their staff member/office.  

That was our last straw and which made up our decision to leave this practice...we felt like the only care this office had was in collecting payment for a service rendered versus trying to make right the error that was made by their office.  

Currently, this office lacks consistent, competent managed care and we hope we are the last Clients that receive this kind of care because San Roque Pet Hospital used to be awesome.

A positive: 
My husband stayed with this office because of the excellent and empathetic care we have received in the past by Dr. Katie Sahyouni.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text:
I can't believe I'm giving a Best Western four stars, but here it is.  The rooms are decently sized and adequately furnished.  The bathrooms are large enough.  Everything seems clean.  Adequate and free hot breakfast.

Great pool and spa.  What really sets this place apart is the landscaping.  They spend a lot of money and time on the gardening and it just makes everything a bit nicer.  

Nice staff.  A good deal here.  

Don't forget to put the "do not disturb" magnetic sign on your door's exterior before you go to bed, or the housekeeper will pound on the door at 8 am to clean your room!

text:
THE place to go if you're in the area and need an elaborate costume fast for a New Year's part, stage debut, anything. 

At Victorian Vogue you can find epoque costumes and really anything. I have rented a Spanish-style long red dress with black corset, a medieval gown, angel costume... 

They have a huge selection and you are unlikely to go home empty-handed. 

It is convenient to be able to rent such clothing because, save for a small fraction of Yelpers, an angel costume does not make its way into your permanent wardrobe. 

The staff has seen it all so if you need to be a cave woman, they're right on top of it!

For things like makeup and fangs, obviously buy, don't rent.

The vanilla bean had plenty of vanilla bean flecks and tasted very much like fresh milk, so if you prefer a more milky taste this is the flavor for you. My husband and I always say that if their base flavor vanilla bean is good, then the ice cream place can be considered good. 

My husband got vanilla bean in a waffle cone, though the waffle cone was not good. To me, tasted like a burnt fortune cookie and kind of ruined the flavor of the ice cream. Overall, the flavors and consistency of the ice cream was on point and we would definitely come back.

text:
I was seriously intrigued to visit this little cafe because of its classic name & fashionable social media pics & posts, however I cannot strongly say that it lived up to the name. 

For starters "the breakfast culture club" has no real breakfast options. There are a couple delectable treats in their display case but nothing you could call a substantial or even healthy breakfast meal choice. 

The coffee was definitely fresh and did hit the spot but not my favorite by any means and really just an average Cup o Joe.

If you're looking for a totally rad hipster joint to spend an extra buck for a mediocre latte & get some cool pictures & free stickers in the process then this is your place.

name: Lee's Tailoring
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Local Services, Sewing & Alterations
text:
I went to Lee's Tailoring because of the many amazing reviews on Yelp and was highly disappointed. The place is small, crowded, and unorganized. Nobody greeted me, smiled at me, or even acknowledged when I came in through the door. I stood there for a few seconds and actually had to shout "Hello" not once but twice until somebody noticed me. The crazy thing about that experience was that there was a receptionist behind the desk and a man standing about three feet away from me yet I, the only customer, had to shout out more than once for attention. I was appalled.

I brought a pair of jeggings in because the zipper was broken. The man who was helping me, whom I assume is Lee, took it in and told me to come back in six days which I wasn't too fond of either. I have an alterations lady I go to back at home which usually completes bigger projects from me in only a few days. Here's the scary part - he charged me $29. $29 to fix a zipper on a pair of jeggings?! The jeggings I bought were from Nordstrom and weren't very expensive to begin with so for a few more dollars I could've bought a brand new pair. Ridiculous. At my other alterations place I would've been charged at most $10 for quicker service too. 

Finally, after I told my boyfriend how much Lee's Tailoring charged me to repair a zipper, he convinced me to go back and get a refund because the price was just crazy.

The receptionist, I think her name's Martha or something along those lines, was very quiet, aloof, and did nothing whatsoever to help me. She barely made eye contact with me. The man, however, was nice enough to offer to write a check and mail it to me (he claimed that a refund back to my card was too much of a hassle... what?!) but I just wanted to get out of there so I gave him my address and agreed. I'll be waiting for my check in the mail I guess.

Let me know if I'm being irrational and if you think $29 isn't too expensive to pay for fixing a zipper on a pair of jeggings. I honetly wouldn't pay more than $10.

Pros: none
Cons: customer service, price, decor, and pretty much everything
Verdict: I'll never go back there again and I definitely don't recommend it based on my experience.

categories: Restaurants, Sushi Bars
text:
PLEASE READ: They have sanitation issues! 

First off this was my FIRST time going in.........so first impressions are everything. Right off the bat it was nice and mellow, the service was mediocre nothing special. The food was alright nothing special as far as beef and noodles go....But what got me the most and this is why this has a one star rating! 

I finished my bowl and at the end of it I noticed a lonely fly floating in my soup.....obviously I was skeptical maybe it flew in towards the end.....the matter of fact was it could of been under all the noodles. There were no flies where I was seated and I have hair past my shoulders which I never once noticed a strand of my own hair in my soup......when I brought it up to the waitress she asked around and all they could do was give me half off.......First off the customer is always right this is by far disgusting, I have never had this happen to me and the fact I could of been eating other flies in my own dish is just horrendous......they couldn't give me one bowl for free is also a lack of responsibility on their part. I even took a picture for reference....

Growing up in SB, I have never had food issues like this.......question your value, SB has many more establishments that respect the customer.

name: Eureka!
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BestNights': "{'monday': False, 'tuesday': True, 'friday': True, 'wednesday': False, 'thursday': False, 'sunday': False, 'saturday': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'CoatCheck': 'False', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HappyHour': 'True', 'Smoking': "u'no'", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'GoodForDancing': 'False', 'Corkage': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Music': "{'dj': False, 'background_music': False, 'no_music': False, 'jukebox': False, 'live': False, 'video': False, 'karaoke': False}", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'GoodForMeal': "{u'breakfast': False, u'brunch': False, u'lunch': True, u'dinner': True, u'latenight': None, u'dessert': False}"}
categories: Restaurants, American (Traditional), Lounges, Nightlife, Bars, Burgers, American (New)
text:
People, let me lay it down for you. I was a MAJOR Eureka fan. My boyfriend and I went on our first date here for Pete's sake. The ambiance is unbeatable and the music selection is awesome. Otherwise, this place officially sucks the big one. Here's why:

It was a rainy Thursday night and we felt like somewhere cozy with a fun atmosphere. Eureka ticks those boxes. 

When we walked in, two rather surly 20-something dudes with man buns rolled their eyes and asked my boyfriend "how many". No "Welcome to Eureka, how can we help you?" That should have been the first red flag.

We shrugged it off and put our names down for the 15 minute wait time as told by Man Bun #1. We also have the app that allows you to track your place in line so we figured we'd go brave the rain and wait for our table outside.

Fast forward this party train to 45 minutes later.  I eat out a lot, I am a frequent restaurant goer. I understand that hosts "guestimate" how long a wait will be and I am a generally patient patron when it comes to wait times. When we walked back in, neither Man Bun #1 or #2 acknowledged our existence as they were too busy wiping down menus. At this time, there was no one waiting in the waiting area and there appeared to be empty tables. Our app said we were "next in line". We asked politely how much longer they thought our wait would be and was given the nonchalant answer of "there's a table you can have now". Cool so...were you planning on utilizing your texting system or.....just not letting us know about our table ever...

We sat down at our table after being given our sticky menus (were they using honey water to clean these??) and were approached by our equally surly 20-something waitress who had the opening greeting of "Drinks?". No name, no how are you, nada. At that point, I had pretty much lost whatever cool I had left and promptly stormed out of the restaurant. Hungry, irritated, and offended I decided that sorry Eureka. I pay to have an enjoyable experience at a restaurant and I will not be paid to be treated like absolute crap. Pretty sad considering I used to be one of their biggest fans. We ended up eating at the Public  Market which I highly recommend for actual customer service and delicious food.

categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Fast Food, Tex-Mex, Restaurants, Mexican, Tacos
text:
I own a Taco Bell hoodie. I'm not kidding. I do. So I'm really not sure that you're going to get an unbiased review of any Taco Bell location from me. Maybe if the store ran out of tacos, I would drill their Star status down, but like all of these outfits, this store is what you expect it to be. 

That said, let me tell you a little awesome story... 

I walked in and ordered my 5 tacos because that's what I love to get when nobody is looking. Taco Bell is my little secret spot I sneak into. I also order a medium Diet Coke. Ok. I gave the lady a $100 bill she couldn't break. I only had cash for the 5 tacos. I skipped the drink and paid for the tacos. She gave me the drink for free. 

See? This small human display of kindness goes a long way and doesn't get forgotten about.
