name: Spa Concepts Salon
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'False', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}
categories: Nail Salons, Threading Services, Skin Care, Eyebrow Services, Beauty & Spas, Hair Removal
text:
I first heard of Dee at Spa Concepts through an Indian friend that had gone to her starting a couple months ago.  I don't have much hair and my brows grow slowly.  However, they were in need for a little cleaning up, so I went.  

The first time I went, she said she was going to just shape it so that it looked presentable.  She wanted more hair to work with so she told me I'd have to come back possibly 3 times at least with 2 months in between each visit.  I agreed.  She did ok on my first visit.  The brows looked ok.  When I got home, my right brow looked slightly higher than the left brow.  I went back to her and she told me to let it grow out so she can work with it.  Fair enough.  I ended up drawing in my eyebrows to compensate.

On my second visit 2 months later, she got to see the amount of growth on my brows, and proceeded to shape it.  After she was done, both of my brows looked too thin.  I was a bit disappointed because I had much more brow to work with after 2 months.  After I got home, I noticed that my right eye brow was still higher than my left (despite my telling her beforehand that this needed correcting).  I also noticed that my right brow and my left brow looked like they had different shapes (one had a smooth arch and the other had more of an angle) and both weren't looking symmetrical.  Again, I went back to her to show her what she did.  She said to allow it to grow out and that my brows will really take shape on the third try.  She convinced me that it takes 3 tries to fully get it the way it should be.  Like a dummy, I decided to give her another chance and told myself maybe she knows what she's talking about.

On my third and final visit another 2 months later, I came back to her and reminded what she did the last 2 times.  She said no problem and got right to work.  I reminded her not to make my brows too thin, to make both symmetrical in shape and in position (height), etc.  She kept nodding and told me not to worry.  After she was done, I was shocked to see what I saw in the mirror.  My brows were basically a thin line (about 1/8 inch only!).  I couldn't believe what I saw!  I confronted her politely but firmly about this, and she only said that that was my true brow line!  WHAT?!  I had much more hair to work with after this 2 month wait, and this is what I got?!?  I went home crying and all my husband could do was hold me.  In addition, after I got home, I noticed that my brows were even less symmetrical and that the arch on the right brow is closer to the middle of my forehead than the brow on the left.  I was very sad and angry.  I've been drawing my eyebrows in ever since.  Sigh...

I will never go back to Dee again!  Let this be a warning.  That 3-time thing she told me about likely was a scam.  She charges $20 (cash only!) each time (expensive for brows), and I feel like I really got ripped off.  (She's probably not reporting most of her earnings to the IRS.)  And what is this name she uses "Dee's Spa Concepts"? There is nothing spa-like about her facility...no other spa services offered and her business place is the size of a closet.  I kept trying to give her the benefit of the doubt, but now I'm out of patience.  I'm going to try Layla (downtown Santa Barbara in the Paseo Nuevo Plaza) the next time I need my brows cleaned up.

text:
Five of us had dinner at High Sierra tonight and all were pleased. Three had hamburgers  - Mushroom, Blue Cheese and Sourdough. Two of us had fish and chips. Lots of food. Fish had a nice batter that was the right degree of crispness - not the mushy stuff you get some places. The tarter was bland - but then I zip mine up with Tabasco and horseradish. Malt vinegar and lemon helped. Service was pleasant and attentive. Prices were reasonable. We'll go back, maybe try the back-ribs, which others have said are excellent.
I might add, the French fries were average - a thicker slice might be recommended. Nothing wrong, maybe my personal preference for fewer, larger fries that hold heat longer and provide more mouth-feel. Really, a nit that doesn't detract from the overall positive.

categories: Lounges, Bars, American (New), Nightlife, Modern European, Restaurants
text:
Walked in on a Saturday night after a day of wine tasting in Santa Ynez, and my group was seated immediately (we called ahead to let them know we were on our way).

Menu leans toward the French tip (think Escargot, Steamed Mussels, Beef Bourguignon).  The dining room is open - the walls decorated with diamond shaped, framed drawings that I assume were done by customers/friends of the restaurant.

We started with the fried calamari and steak tartare.  The calamari was your standard lightly breaded variety that came with a side of aioli.  Steak Tartare was good, a small portion of raw ground beef and chopped onion with other herbs/seasonings, served with arugula and bread.

For entrees, I ordered the Mahogany Short Ribs with Baby Bok Choy, and a side of the garlic mashed potatoes.  The short ribs were good, especially when paired with the mashed potatoes, which everyone at the table LOVED.  Probably the smoothest non-fake mashed potatoes I've ever had.

Definitely a great choice when dining in SB.

categories: Nightlife, Pubs, Beer, Wine & Spirits, American (Traditional), Burgers, Bars, Food, Restaurants
text:
AMAZING! 
Now the natural comparison would be to Eureka! Burger but really the two have little in common beyond outstanding burgers, beer and whiskey. 

American Ale is a dark pub with no table service. You order your burgers at the bar and a food runner brings them out (very quickly and efficiently I might add). 

Eureka has many appetizers and excellent entree salads; American Ale does one thing phenomenally well: burgers. Eureka! reportedly spent half a million on the decor/interior and it's bright without being obnoxiously cheery. 

But I am angry at Eureka for taking my favorite burger--the Caprese--off the menu . American Ale offers burgers for the bacon lover as well as carnivores who dislike bacon or who at the very least who would never dream of putting bacon on a burger.

My boyfriend loves the three bacon burger (two are bacon proper, one is Canadian bacon, aka ham which I just plain can't bear under any conditions unlike bacon which on occasion I like in a BLT or a Cobb salad--or the Wolfgang's salad in NYC in Murray Hill on 33rd and Park). 

I don't eat fries as a rule but I had some and they were excellent. They don't have onion rings, which Eureka does perfectly. 

I also don't drink beer but had an IPA I loved in a cute glass jar. 

I love whiskey but didn't have any as I'd had white wine before dinner and in my experience white wine is hangover juice period but certain death when  mixed with beer and whiskey within the same 24 hour period. 

My horseradish and blue cheese burger blew my mind and I will be back. 

As good as Umami burger, which is now my standard of comparison but far sleeker.

text: Wonderful hotel in the perfect location. Easy walk to State Street and a nice jog down to the beach. The rooms are clean and the staff is very attentive. We will definitely be staying here for future visits to Santa Barbara. And the muffins are amazing as well!!!!

Came again last night. It was packed but managed to get table in bar. Waitress was attentive and service was impeccable despite it being crazy busy.

text: We've been here twice. First time I remember being fine - not great, not bad. Second time, we walked in and saw that the tasting menu was more whites than reds (we prefer reds) but since the place was empty (Sunday noon), we didn't feel right walking out. So we just shared a tasting. The person was really nice and informative. We sat by the window as we tasted and he even came out to pour for us which was really nice. (We usually just taste and go back to the counter for the next one.) It was a very nice experience. Too bad we didn't particularly like either of the wines tasted. Maybe next time one will hit the spot. Either way, AVA is a nice place to visit.

text: This has become my favorite sandwich(& cookie) spot in SB..  First of all, the Gyros are to die for. Thy are packed with meat, fresh veggies, and awesome tzatziki sauce! While the line can get long at lunchtime, their sandwiches are worth the wait. I usually order a half sandwich and grab a cookie to go and that is the perfect size! They also have tons of homemade deli options that I am waiting to try soon! Mmm what a gem!

name: Pueblo Radiology Medical Group
attributes: {'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'AcceptsInsurance': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Radiologists, Health & Medical, Doctors, Diagnostic Imaging, Diagnostic Services, Medical Centers
text: i had a great experience getting my open MRI done few days ago. The receptionist was very professional on the phone and let me know of my copay ( I'm glad she did that, it would have been a big surprise for me!) Then when I arrived at the office she was friendly & handled my paperwork quickly. The technician who took my MRI did his best to make me feel comfortable ( I'm claustrophobic and get anxious) he explained every step & even played music for me so that I get distracted. The place was very clean, new and up to date. My records were forwarded to both my doctors right away. I was very satisfied with their services, I know I would go there again if I need to have any kind of imaging done!

text: I had the pleasure of booking with Luxe transportation for my birthday weekend in Santa Barbara. A group of us went wine tasting in Los Olivos for the first time. I wish I would of gone sooner, we had such an amazing time!! The bus itself was very spacious, clean and even had an aux so you could play your own music. The bus driver David was amazing when it came to taking pictures of the group and captured many memories for us to remember forever. If you're looking for a good time with friends, I highly recommend Luxe Transportation!!!

name: Ala Mar Motel
attributes: {'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Hotels, Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel
text: While the jacuzzi tub was very nice, I couldn't overlook the overall shortcomings of the room.   The toilet was in a space so small that your knees will be only a few inches from the door when seated. The door did not have a lock, or even close completely.  There was no closet, only a rod hanging above the dresser with two hangers.  There were missing tiles & the door & window moldings had been replaced, but not painted.   The ceiling fan had a missing cover over one of the lights.  The wifi didn't work. There was no hairdryer.  The tub  & shower are out in the open, so if you're traveling with someone you would rather not see you bathing that should be kept in mind.  I think this may have been a nice place at one time, I cannot recommend it.  It needs some major renovations.

name: Tint Works Window Tinting
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True'}
categories: Auto Glass Services, Auto Customization, Automotive, Home Services, Home Window Tinting, Car Window Tinting
text:
I had the pleasure of getting my car tinted by Jaime this past week. It's taken me several months to find a place that I trusted to work on my Tesla Model S. After reading reviews and hearing great things about Jaime's work, I finally decided to get my car done. I dropped my car off in the morning and he told me that it'd be ready in about 3 hours. When I came to pick up my car, I could tell that he took his time to make sure everything looked great. 
I highly recommend anyone whose looking to get their car tinted to get it done by Jaime. He won't disappoint!

name: Kimpton Canary Hotel
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'paid'", 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3'}
categories: Event Planning & Services, Hotels & Travel, Venues & Event Spaces, Hotels
text:
We had an awesome experience at this boutique hotel. This hotel has top notch service and supports sustainability. The hotel front desk even communicates with text and you can ask for items, ask for recommendations, etc this way. We received a discount on overnight parking because we drove a hybrid. This hotel is really dog friendly, not only this but there is no additional charge to bring your dog (no size restrictions) AND they even allow you to leave your dog in your room if need be (as long as your dog is not barking, etc). I have NEVER before come across a hotel that allows you to do this. The associated restaurant/bar downstairs is hip and the bar seems to allow dogs too!

The hotel really makes you feel special. In fact, Helen at the front desk even left us a gift of a framed photo of our dog in the hotel. It was a very nice surprise. We were not hotel rewards members and had booked off Expedia, but after our all around great experience, we signed up for their reward program because we will be back!

Perks:
Free happy hour daily in the lobby with local beer, wine and appetizers
Attached restaurant 
Friendly and attentive staff
Super duper dog friendly (the only thing is that there is not any grass on or around the property for bathroom access for your pet)
Access to next door gold's gym 

Location:
In the downtown area, so everything is walkable. This is not a waterfront property, but there is a view of the ocean from the lovely rooftop pool area. 

Note: if you aren't a dog person, this hotel is probably not for you, as there are lots of dogs hanging out at this hotel.

text: We have driven by Rincon Brewery many times, but have always been on our way somewhere. Today, we were looking for a place for lunch and noticed the patio was almost empty right before noon - perfect! Found a quick parking place on the street and chose a place on the patio. Great clean patio, nice view of the street and people passing by. I opted for one of their daily specials, the Cali Burrito - essentially a steak burrito with guacamole, pico de gallo, cheese and french fries....yes, french fries. It came with a side of baked tortilla chips and a great homemade salsa. Would definitely be back next time we are in town!

categories: Music Venues, Bars, Nightlife, Arts & Entertainment, Restaurants, American (Traditional)
text: Was here the other night to see a DJ. About half way through the night I noticed someone in our group was missing and checked my phone--he texted me saying he was kicked out because they thought he was washing off his "X's" (they use sharpie to mark huge X's on both hands indicating you're not 21 yet). I went outside and asked the usher kindly to let him back. The usher got very angry and threatened to kick me out as well. I went back inside to test the theory and successfully washed both X's off--PURPOSEFULLY--and did not get in trouble (you still need to have a wristband or ID to get drinks). Went back out again to talk to the usher and another worker comes up behind me and SHOVES me outside. Basically I learned this place would rather be 21+ ONLY so I'm not sure why they even bother mixing the 18+ crowd in there, and a huge screw you to whoever felt the need to shove me from behind outside, you're lucky I wasn't hurt or there would be a lawsuit present.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'None'}
categories: Beer, Wine & Spirits, Wineries, Food, Arts & Entertainment
text:
This places was very cute!
My bridesmaid took me here to kick off my bachlorette weekend. 

Overall: Good wine and great atmosphere to sip on some wine.

Location: It's on a street near other breweries and other wineries. A lot of places were within walking distance. 

Parking: 
We took an uber here, so I'm not sure about the parking situation, but to me it looked like it was street parking, I'm unsure if they had their own lot. 

Wine: I don't remember the prices, if I remember correct, It was $15 for 5 tastings. ( I didn't pay for it, so don't quote me. haha) 
I got to choose from whites, reds or mixed. I chose to try out the mixed tastings.

What I liked: The wine was delicious, they would tell you what you were having before they poured into your wine glass. They also let you keep the wine glass at the end! (They even wrapped it into tissue paper and gave you a bag for it.) 
We sat indoors but I think there was outdoor/patio sitting in the front of the winery if I remember correctly.

They also have this cat that roams around the winery. It's so cute and friendly!!

text: If you are in SB and like uni, this is THE place. Or so we were told (haha). We got two unis and 4 oysters of the day (blue point?). Since we're still in school, although a higher level, we qualified for the student discount of 20%! YES! See kids, getting your higher higher education is truly worth it. The SB uni is sweet and since I basically ate both unis' because R decided he just wasn't into eating it by itself. Oysters were good too. Great place to stop by. Remember to bring some cash to tip the workers. He was super nice and spent a lot of time cleaning the uni and putting them together.

name: Ronald B Dinning, DMD
attributes: {'AcceptsInsurance': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Health & Medical, Dentists, General Dentistry, Cosmetic Dentists
text:
Not big on doing reviews so this says something. Throughout my life I hated going to the dentist, mostly due to my lack of confidence in the person handling my teeth. I will say Dr. Dinning is a super nice guy who really knows his stuff and shows that he cares for you and your oral health. Does a proper and clean job for a more than reasonable price for the work he does. He clearly has loads of experience. I would recommend anyone to come in for general/complex cosmetic work, repairs, and especially assessments which are very thorough. 
Furthermore, the office is very understanding on the financial side as well. Apart from reasonable pricing, I was able to set up a monthly plan to pay off my bill over time which I am not used to seeing elsewhere. 
The accompanying staff match the work ethic and charisma of Dr. Dinning.

text:
This is probably the only Thai restaurant in Goleta so we decided to get our fix. The do have a lot of options to chose from. Ended up getting Pad See Ouw with tofu, and egg rolls. The sauce for the egg rolls was a little bizarre, it gave me and my roommate a weird cough after eating it, and not because it was spicy. 
I liked that they made the noodles a little crispy for the Pad See Ouw.
The major downfall of this place is the atmosphere. The walls are tacky with not many decorations, and parts of the restaurant smelled like public bathroom cleaner. Kinda gross. They need to give this place a really really big face lift so people can focus on the good food.

text: The drinks are watered down, so even with their happy hour 2 for 1 special you don't even get a buzz.  I guess this a way to keep the just-turned 21 SBCC and UCSB crowd to buy more drinks without turning sloppy.  Now, if just the drinks were crappy that would be one thing but we ate there the other night and my bean and cheese Tostada tasted like something had gone completely sour.  Literally, it tasted like sour, curdled milk.  I asked my boyfriend to smell it and just the foul scent made him lose his appetite.  When I told the server she took it to the kitchen and came back to tell us that they use a sauce on some of their dishes that might have a similar scent.  I replied that there was no way this could be the sauce, unless that had also gone bad.  I had a terribly upset stomach for the next two days....

name: Big Joe's Tacos
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Food Trucks, Event Planning & Services, Mexican, Street Vendors, Caterers, Restaurants, Food
text:
I was lucky to try Big Joe's tacos at a birthday party I attended. I had no idea about them and asked if they are local here in Santa Barbara. Turns out they are based here but do cater out of town as well. 

The menu for this event was as follows: 

Tacos ~ 
Carne asada 
chorizo 
adobada 
chicken
grilled veggies 

They were all delicious! The meats were very well seasoned and not too salty. I just wish the servings of meat were a bit more as they were pretty skimpy. Especially the chicken. It was finely chopped so it almost seemed like bits of ground chicken. I would give these 3.0 stars for the portions but 4 stars for flavor.

Sides ~ 
Mexican rice
pinto beans
chips and guac
salsa

The mexican rice was your traditional rice but it had good flavor and wasn't dry. It was cooked perfectly. The beans were just plain pintos but those are the best when combined with the rice and some salsa to spice it up! 

The chips n guac were just ok. I mostly enjoyed the chips because they were homemade and not too greasy or salty. The guac didn't seem to be authentic but more like the stuff you get pre-packaged in the store. It tasted good despite not being the real deal. 

There were 5 different salsas to choose from. I tried them all and mixed the mild ones with a few drops of the habañero as suggested by Angel the taco guy. I pretty much put each salsa on everything cuz afterall who doesn't love salsa! They were all freshly made and had good flavor. The medium one was a bit watery though. Aside from that I enjoyed each one. 

Quesadillas were also served upon request. I couldn't get over how delicious the chorizo quesadilla was! And the chorizo wasn't too greasy as it tends to be. Such great flavor! I really enjoyed this.

Angel and Diana catered this event and they were very professional and kind enough to explain each food item being served. Their set up was great too! 

Overall if you're looking for a taquero to cater your next event give Big Joe's a try! They really did a great job.

name: Sal's Pizza
attributes: {'Alcohol': "'beer_and_wine'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: Chicken Wings, Restaurants, Italian, Pizza
text:
I picked Sal's Pizza after reading reviews of several Santa Barbara pizza deliveries.  Without much poetry, I must say.... Sal's is the worst pizza I've ever tasted. It was so bad, I had to open a Yelp account just so I could set the story straight.  

I wish I could give it a positive review.  I just moved here, and am looking for my go-to pizza joint.  However, Sal's Pizza is as bad as frozen pizza. I was disappointed in the taste and texture of this pizza.  The crust was flavorless, and had that weird crispy/soggy thing.... overly crunchy outer crust, and soggy under the toppings.  No "bite, no bubbles.  BAD.  The sauce had too much oregano, not enough tomato flavor.  Too dark, not fresh tasting at all.  The toppings (I ordered caramelized onions, italian sausage and fresh ricotta cheese) were abundant enough, though there was not a lot of cheese on it.... kind of like a frozen pizza.

I also ried the garlic bread.  I liked that they offered free mozzarella cheese on the garlic bread - but i decided to have it without the cheese (assuming there would be plenty on the pizza).  The bread was greasy and very salty- as if it was flavored only with garlic salt.  

I've had a lot of pizza throughout the years.  Some delicious, some mediocre.  But i've never had a pizza from a Pizzeria that I wanted to throw away.  Sal's Pizza is the first.  Please, DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY.  This place stinks.

categories: Restaurants, American (New), Seafood, Steakhouses
text: A romantic culinary dream. Located up in the incredible Montecito hills, surrounded by wealth, class, and luxury, up in San Ysidro Ranch. Our anniversary was well spent last night, here at Stonehouse. The twinkle lights enveloped the patio as night fell creating a beautiful ambiance! Our waiter Adrian spent the evening taking care of us and was exceptionally knowledgable. The wine was paired perfectly with our dishes. We ordered the Diver Scallops as an appetizer which, if you love scallops, were breathtaking. Followed by the special for the evening, a Pan Seared Tuna, and I ordered the much anticipated Halibut dish, of which did not disappoint. The chocolate soufflé, a gooey delectable treat that, in my opinion, would be worth the visit all on its own. Will absolutely return, will remember this evening forever, and will stay at the hotel next time! Tip- get there early and walk the grounds, beautiful views!

text: Fantastic new coffee spot in Goleta.  Bigger and bolder than Goleta Coffee Company just not quite as much parking - BUT - there is plenty of free parking one block away at the Community West Bank.  It is worth the walk.  Great coffee, pastries -  I had a brioche sort of a roll filled with melted cheese and prosciutto, a good light breakfast item.   With a large comfortable space, hopefully they will add sandwiches soon.  If they would just put a sign about parking they would get much busier, maybe that's NOT a good idea, LOL.  (I really mourned the closing of the Worker Bee Cafe a few blocks away in the old Sizzler center but this makes it much better!.)   Really beautiful inside.  Lovely place to meet friends, or just relax for a minute with a really nice cuppa joe.  Oh wow, just noticed in another review that there is an outside area too?  Oyvay!

text:
Well, they do have the best price and they do perform the repair quickly.  However, the quality is a bit lacking.

I've had two windshields replaced by them on two different cars.  Both times, the replacement windshields fog up EASILY.  I'm talking, hop in the car on a misty day, take 3 breaths, and the windshield is fogged up.  Neither of the original windshields fogged up anywhere near this easily.

Also, their workmanship is not great.  The second windshield they replaced, they broke lots of plastic & rubber trim surrounding the windshield and left most of it loose for me to discover & fix myself.

text:
Nugget Bar & Grill

Decided to check this place out for dinner with the guys while we were out here in Goleta working on a project. 

The place is not huge and the parking, let's face it is even worse so plan accordingly. The wait was not long surprisingly even for a party of 4. 

They did happen to take a while to get our drink order and by the time the waiter came through we ordered our meal as well. Our food came out shockingly fast. 

Everything was picturesque to say the least, but full of flavor. Everything from burgers to fried chicken was cooked perfectly. 

The ambience seemed to say it was more of a local hangout spot for all ages and the place to be even on a Thursday night. Nonetheless it was a decent night and I would probably still come back again.

text: Stopped into Night Lizard Brewing as we were walking on state street. They had a cool name and we thought we would check them out. We did try a couple of samples and decided on the Monkeyflower Double White Ale which was delicious on this warm afternoon. We wanted to stay and have more beer, but most of their options had been rotated out and the choices were limited. While walking and shopping along state street, I do recommend stopping by Night Lizard Brewing to see if they have more beer on tap and then have a seat on their patio and watch the people go by.

categories: Event Planning & Services, Latin American, Caterers, Food, Restaurants, Empanadas, Argentine
text:
My friend and I stopped by here on a whim to try someplace new. As soon as we pulled into the parking lot we noticed how lively the ambiance was outdoors, with a flat screen TV showing some soccer game and plenty of people having a good laugh.

We were pretty hungry so we started with half a dozen empanadas - Serrano, Hongos, Suiza, and a few other flavors. Each and every empanada we tried was a bite out of heaven, and the chimichurri sauce elevated the flavors to another level! We had to go back in to order more of the Serranos along with some tiramisu to wrap things up.

10/10 would recommend to anyone for a delicious brunch and top-notch coffee with a side of soccer!

name: Neurofield Neurotherapy
attributes: {'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'AcceptsInsurance': 'True'}
categories: Doctors, Health & Medical, Naturopathic/Holistic
text:
I have suffered with issues around anxiety, what I refer to as low grade depression, due to childhood trauma that I experienced.  In addition, in my mid fifties I started to notice a slight decline in mental acuity.

As a patient of Dr. Thompson, my experience has been one of profound healing, for myself and for my son.

After getting my brain map done, Dr Thompson and I were both able to see how my issues could improve through a combination of Neuro modulation while also having a talk therapy session.

Over the course of this past year my overall appreciation for life and general well being has increased, very little anxiety left, and little to no further depression.  Mental acuity has also improved, I feel like I can perform in my work like I did before, perhaps even better now.

My son had been labelled as ADD in elementary school.  He did struggle with school, but managed to do pretty well.  In college he was only able to pull solid grades from the film classes he took, otherwise he tended to tank.  He also had a very difficult time holding down a part time job.  

When my son met Dr Thompson, she determined that his brain profile did not match up with the typical profile of Adult ADD, but that he had a low voltage profile that could be improved upon.

In addition to the neuro modulation that he received, Dr Thompson worked with Adam and got him to find excitement in what he was most interested in and passionate about, which was and is screenwriting.

So the proof in the pudding here, is that my son enrolled in a screen writing BFA program four years ago in Los Angeles and in a few months he will graduate with that BFA! He also has had the same part time job for the last couple of years, running an escape room in Hollywood.  Huge progress!  

Any parent who has a child that they feel like they are really struggling to function, knows what a relief it is to see them start to thrive!

I am very proud of his accomplishments AND I am forever grateful to Dr. Thompson and her team, for finding the path that is allowing this young mans amazing creativity to be coming alive personally and professionally!

I have referred my friends to Dr Thompson, and have gotten rave reviews back from them as well.

We are very fortunate to have this clinic, Dr Thompson, Dr Dogris, and their staff here in our community!

text: It's the standard college spot that has happy hour deals, which are pretty good. We went for lunch on Friday and had 4 Greygoose and RedBulls, and one a la cart taco, our bill was $80. They charge double for the Goose and Bulls and don't give you a heads up. You get charged for the Greygoose drink, plus an extra $6 for redbull, but they use a new can each time, so you get to pay $10 to drink out of a plastic dixie cup that they used a jigger to pour. Stick to happy hour here, you'll need the 2 for 1, the drink's hardly have any alcohol.

text: In search for a cake for my sister in law's shower I stumbled into The Little Things Bakery and I'm so glad I did.  I ordered an 8 inch vanilla cake and since we don't like super sweet cakes I asked for a naked style cake, with peaches, strawberries and kiwi fresh fruit, whipped cream filling with almond extract, and buttercream icing. Everyone, this cake was delicious!!!! All the girls in the party loved it. Thank you Little Things Bakery for the delicious treat.

text:
AVOID THIS PLACE AT ALL COSTS!
The worst so called BBQ we ever ate in our life!

We ordered take out and ordered 
a chicken dinner and a pulled pork sandwich. Both came with fries.
The chicken looked delicious but was so dry and flavorless we threw it out. 
The pork sandwich was served on a huge bun and it was barely two tablespoons of meat. 
Neither meats had any smoke flavor and the pork appeared boiled. 
The fries were supposed to be "freshly hand cut" but were nearly black and cold and had been cooked for some time.
NEVER GOING BACK!!

text:
Yes. Just yes.

I went to the public market with a group so that everyone could choose what they wanted to eat. Walking around, I ended up getting a beer at The Garden and my food from Empty Bowl. No regrets at all! 

I ended up ordering the Bangkok Street Noodle to go. Noodles with beef balls all soaking in this delicious spicy, savory and slightly sweet broth. It definitely hit the spot and was exactly what I was craving. 

I'd love to come back here and try out some of the other dishes on their menu. It was hard making a choice at all! Would definitely recommend this for anyone who likes Thai food done with a twist.

text: This place is horrible.  It may look interesting but the massage rooms are FREEZING!!!  I had a massage and I kept telling the masseuse it was freezing in the room.  She agreed and said it is always cold in here.  I have had many massages in my life and it is always supposed to be warm because your body temp drops when you relax.  This is like a cave and it is so cold that I ended up sick. I had to go to the doctor.  I contacted the management which was horrible!!  They basically ignored me.  after over a month of emailing them and calling them the girl finally told me the owner wasn't going to do anything!   I just can not believe it.  She would not even call me back to speak to me about the problem.  To say the least this ended up being an expensive massage that really wasn't worth.  Go some place else...there definitely are much better places in town with good management and warm rooms!!

name: Scott Dewhirst, MD -  Sansum Clinic
categories: Psychics, Arts & Entertainment, Health & Medical, Psychiatrists, Supernatural Readings, Doctors
text: Dr. Dewhirst has worked closely with my other doctors to ensure my mental healthcare is very well taken care of for several years now. He has helped save my life more than once. When I moved out of town this year, he agreed to continue seeing me via telemedicine indefinitely, which was extremely important to me when deciding whether or not to move. If my insurance ever stops covering telehealth, I'll either pay out of pocket or drive to Santa Barbara (a 200-mile round trip) every few months for my appointments, despite that I live in LA surrounded by other psychiatrists. THAT is how excellent of a doctor he is. I always feel like he is on my side, an ally. He goes out of his way to take care of my mental health and is very supportive. He is also highly skilled with polypharmacy (managing multiple medications), which is necessary for me personally, while he also makes sure to never over-medicate. He always takes my opinions and feelings into consideration when making treatment decisions. Bonus: he is always on time! He is worth the very long waitlist.

categories: Modern European, Nightlife, Bars, Restaurants, Bakeries, Wine Bars, Food, Scandinavian, Breakfast & Brunch
text:
I really struggled with rating this restaurant. Torn between 2 stars and 3 stars, and ultimately chose to give it 2 stars because I think the quality of food weighs more than the service. 

Although the service was great (and I did like the free danishes they handed out in the beginning), sadly, the food was just terrible. I ordered the Sir Matthew pork patty, which was a HUGE disappointment considering it was supposed to be their speciality. The pork patty was meh, the sauce was overbearing and nothin special. And the worst part was the country potatoes. Oh man, they were soggy. Just terrible.

My husband ordered one of their breakfast croissant sandwich, and without taking a bite, I can assure that it didn't taste good. The sandwich came out totally smooshed. The delicate beauty of a croissant is the air, the fluffiness. They killed that. Plus, he asked for his egg to be over easy but it came out totally well done and over cooked.

I'm getting the feeling that most restaurants on State Street are bleh. Their level of service, however, is amazing.

I will never come back. Sorry!

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'DogsAllowed': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': None, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': None, 'brunch': None, 'breakfast': None}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BYOB': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'None', 'HappyHour': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}"}
categories: American (Traditional), Seafood, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Burgers, Breakfast & Brunch
text:
Much love for On The Alley, the food is delicious and relatively inexpensive! I would come here all the time when I was a college student for a quick meal. From burgers to breakfast burritos to Brophy Bros. classics, this casual harbor eatery has everything everybody will enjoy. Some of the menu items I've tried:

Fish & Chips - Always served piping hot and fresh out of the fryer. The batter is light and airy, with just enough crunch every bite. Perfectly flakey fish as well.

Clam Chowder - No need to travel to New England, Seattle, or Pismo! OTA's rendition is super creamy and savory. I'm not too crazy about their sourdough bread, but it satisfies a craving.

Crab Cake Burger - Probably one of their more inconsistent options, the crab cake patty can be a hit or miss when it comes to portion size.

Pulled Pork Sandwich - Generous amounts of slow-roasted pork, I know other places go ham when it comes to adding coleslaw. Thankfully that wasn't the case here.

OTA Burger - Your conventional burger but with a breakfast twist. Fried egg, avocado, and bacon make a very tasty combination.

Definitely a solid joint to visit if you're looking to eat by the water!

name: Bouchon
attributes: {'Corkage': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'BYOBCorkage': "'yes_corkage'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '3', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Caters': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'HappyHour': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': True, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'"}
categories: Seafood, Bars, Wine Bars, American (New), Restaurants, French, Nightlife, Mexican
text:
Love this place.  It's right off of State Street and you might have some trouble parking during dinner time.  I had reservations for 8p and we were seated at 830p (we got there late - around 820p).  The ambiance is more laid back than the French restaurants up North - casual art, yellow walls, open view kitchen that looked like house kitchen, "Fly me to the moon" type of music, etc.  We liked that.

The savory foie gras is AMAZING.  it was on top of beet salad, spiced butternut puree, brioche crouton, and red wine jus.  It was a good sized portion and so buttery.  YUM!   My two friends like the Seared Diver Scallop Trio better.  It was these huge scallops in three ways - as salad, appetizer and then dinner.  We all agreed the salad scallop was the best.  

We had a bottle of the Point Conception chardonnay, which was really good with our appetizers.  By the time our entrees came around, I was full!  I had the duck, which was pretty awesome.  The Wagyu beef was pretty good and the friend that had the Ahi tuna with lemon mashed potatoes literally licked her plate clean.  

I would recommend this place to people of all ages (except kids) for any occasion or non-occasion.  Definitely would come back.  Our waiter (Eric), the host, the waitstaff, and the manager who would get on the chair to take our photos, were all gracious and very customer-service oriented.  The best I've seen in awhile.

One bad thing - they have retired the Blueberry cake for now (even though blueberries are in season).  I was really disappointed.  I don't recommend any desserts here.   Go somewhere else for dessert.

text: My husband, son & I come to this restaurant about once a week. They are a friendly consistent crew with a delicious food & wine selection that never disappoints. My husband loves the tortellini or rib eye with white beans. I love the ravioli with brown sage sauce & the rack of lamb. All of the salads and anti pasta are great. It's a welcoming neighborhood restaurant with a friendly intimate environment where I've never had a bad meal or bad service. It's well managed. The pizzas are really good too. Can't think of a negative thing to say about this consistently lovely & delicious restaurant!

name: Farmer Boy
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'Caters': 'False', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': None, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': True}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HappyHour': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Breakfast & Brunch, Burgers, American (Traditional), American (New), Restaurants
text:
If anything, get the home fries (potatoes) for breakfast. They're the best that I have ever had; nicely seasoned throughout, good crisp. I wish I had the recipe. 
Busboys are not only professional but also friendly, happy and respectful. 
Every waitress has a good knowledge of the menu and can make appropriate recommendations should you want a substitution.  Coffee, water, and hot tea are checked on for refills. The cinnamon roll is about 6" wide so it's enough to split. 
Restaurant is very clean, as well as the restroom. 
Noise can be a little loud but when you have so many people coming in for one of the best breakfasts in town, it's expected. The tables in the back can be moved to accommodate larger parties. 
Very family-friendly, dogs okay outside. 
It's not a huge venue; just an unpretentious diner tucked into the corner of a strip mall on the north side of town.  I would have it no other way.  The food???????

Always excellent. Fresh ingredients. Nothing stale or turning. 

I write this review with a heavy heart because they deserve the accolades; however, I do not look forward to the day when I have to "wait to be seated ". 

God bless you, Farmer Boy!

text:
This is one of the few things I miss about Santa Barbara. I just don't know how to sum up my love for the Natty Cafe. Everything I've ever tried there has given me that good food high, but now, since I'm there like once a year or something, it's gotta be the Good Karma Burger. A tempeh patty with black beans and corn IN THE PATTY! IN THE PATTY, people. And Veganaise and soy cheese. It's so delicious. The smoothies are good, the appetizers (hummus, mmmm) are so good to share. And I just feel all clean and wonderful inside after eating there. 
It reminds of the Saturday war protests I used to go to every week when I lived there, and afterwards my hippy friends and I would scrounge up our change and go to the Natty. Ahhh, my introduction to Hippydom. Good memories.

categories: French, Cafes, Restaurants, Breakfast & Brunch, Food, Sandwiches, Bakeries
text:
I have been to Renaud's on several occasions and I have been very pleased with the food, pastries, and service up until my recent visit. 

We were on our way from Santa Maria and phoned in our order at 2:15pm to dine in at 2:30pm. We specifically requested to dine-in. Once we arrived, we paid the bill and our order was delivered to us in a to-go bag. Okay, fine. The person who took our order over the phone was a female, and the cashier who took our order was the only female in Renaud's. Therefore, one has to assume that the name on the receipt, Kiersten, is the one who received our phone order with instructions to serve the food for dine-in. Once we received our order in a bag, we sat down and unloaded the food on a table. We later found that we did not receive any butter and jam for the croissant. No biggie, I'll get up and ask for some. I ask Kiersten for some butter and jam, and she silently grabs some and hands them to me. I say thank you to her loud and clear, and she ignored me. It's one thing when someone doesn't want to be friendly, but when you are working with customers, I expect some sort of acknowledgement so that I, as a customer, can feel welcome for a small service that I paid for.

We ate our food, and it tasted mediocre which is way less than expected at this establishment. I don't know if our mood was lost, or we received the unwelcome service before the kitchen closed that resulted in poorly tasting food. How unfortunate. In addition to our experience, the other employees were two young males who were both chatting and laughing in a very loud manner as if no one was around. It was a Tuesday afternoon approaching 2:30pm and the kitchen was closing, I get it. However, Renaud's closes at 5pm. Overall, it was an unpleasant experience such that it seemed as though none of the workers wanted to work. Two stars for a one star experience because we had some great experiences in the past.

categories: Restaurants, Bars, Nightlife, Barbeque, Sandwiches
text:
I was excited to try the Wildwood Kitchen but was ultimately disappointed. The restaurant has an appealing aesthetic but the acoustics are terrible. The noise was so loud that we had to shout to hold a conversation. BBQ can be very simple and tasty but, in this case, it was simple, overcooked, and bland. This was particularly annoying because the food was hyped by the wait staff as "really amazing" when it was decidedly not. The drinks were tasty but expensive so, when we got the bill, we felt that the overall price of the meal exceeded the quality. 

It seems something can be done about most of this - improve the food quality, humble the wait staff, for example - but the acoustics might be more tricky. I'd love these folks to succeed here in the "funk zone" of Santa Barbara, particularly because they've obviously invested a lot in putting it together, but I won't be back until I've heard about the improvements.

categories: Seafood, Restaurants, Hawaiian, American (New), Breakfast & Brunch
text:
2020 Peoples Choice (Independent) WINNNNNNNER of:
Best View
Best Bloody Mary
Best Sunday Brunch
Best Happy Hour (bester in the winter)
I agree on all points. Let's discuss.

The best barstool in town and my personal oasis for chill, visit with strangers/regulars and the stellar crew here while staring at the ocean.

Bars love to tout their Bloody Mary's. Here the hype is justified. Not a wet mess but a well rounded, spiced (not necessarily spicy cocktail). Filling and refreshing. Although not my go-to breakfast bevi here, they are worth ordering.

Sunday Brunch or any morning meal at the beach is a WINNER. The gang knows my order:  Step in the Right Direction and the Signature Breakfast. Whatever you choose, you'll always have the view. Which is nice.

Best Happy Hour is where you'll find me. The questions are 1. At what time and 2. For how long? The Boathouse Happy Hour follows the sun. Or more specifically the clock.
Daylight Savings Time (Summer): 3-6 Sunday through Thursday
Winter: 3-Close Sunday through Thursday a s some years a late night Friday option
They specials save you a couple bucks but more importantly is who this brings in. Locals, tourists, regulars, and first timers. I love it.
You'll know me from my signature glass of Chardonnay and fries. Those friend fries may be with the burger, local muscles, or on their own.

If you're a tourist, know there may be long lines to take in the view. For the locals/regulars, we know when to enjoy the patio all to ourselves but always happy to share. As long as you say "hi" when you see me.

Cheers

text: This shop is awesome. I had been walking/jogging along Morro Beach and seemed to have stepped into some tar sands created by Chevron over the past few decades. The smell on my shoes was hideous and I figured that I would need to trash them. However, on a lark we brought the shoes to this shop and the owner and repair team were able to get them cleaned up within an hour. I had tried everything to get the tar off my shoes but it didn't work. I'm not sure how they were able to work their magic, but the shoes are as good as new. I appreciate the fast service and reasonable price.

name: State & Fig
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'beer_and_wine'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': None, 'brunch': None, 'breakfast': None}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'HasTV': 'False', 'Corkage': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BYOB': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}", 'DogsAllowed': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, American (New), Delis, Breakfast & Brunch, Tapas/Small Plates, Cafes
text: As recent transplants we've been on a vigorous and calorically enhanced mission to sample every restaurant in Santa Barbara. We now can declare definitively that STATE & FIG is the best burger. Boom. Start with a lovely brioche bun from a local bakery on De La Vina, the half pound burger is steak quality beef, cooked perfectly (my wife a well done; me a medium), with options that are complex but not silly as is often the case. I chose 'The Fig' with fig jam, grilled onions, arugula and blue cheese, just enough blend of tastes to enhance but not overwhelm the meat. The garlic fries are a revelation -- and if someone could figure a way to deliver them to me when I'm in my jammies watching Colbert eviscerate our clown in the White House, I'd call it heaven. Also noteworthy is a very genial and gregarious staff: in particular, Tracey, a fellow transplant from Pennsylvania who helped my wife figure out where to yoga, to massage, to pedicure and other verbs I'm making up. It's in that cozy courtyard at 1114 State and a great hang out. I don't eat much red meat so when I do, I do not want to waste my sinfulness on stinkiness! This is a better burger than any I've had in L.A. (maybe Pono Burger in Santa Monica is close). On we go exploring -- but this will become a regular stop!

categories: Sushi Bars, Szechuan, Cantonese, Restaurants, Chinese
text:
I tried this place just to try something new. I do have a place in Santa Barbara that I frequent at least once or twice a month, but since it was for New Years I thought, why not try something new? I ordered Kung Pao Chicken and Broccoli Beef for take out. They were good and the portion size was comparable to the portion size to my regular restaurant. Only other issue was I usually pay about $12 an entree and $4-5 for an appetizer and here it was about $16 for an entree and $8-10 for an appetizer. Also, the worst part was when I got home I realized there was no white rice in my order. I was shocked! I called a relative of mine who I knew had dined there very recently and I asked him and he did say they charge extra. FOR RICE! This is the only Chinese place that I can think of that does this. I checked their website listed in my Axxess book, and there is no mention (that I can see) that says there is an extra fee for white rice or that you need to order is separately etc. If I had at least seen a disclaimer or something I would have ordered it. I did not feel like driving all the way back to buy some since it was already late in the evening on New Years eve so my family and I just had the entrees by themselves, with no rice. 

Pros: Tasty, Good portion size
Cons: Need to pay extra for rice, overpriced

My suggestion to the owners would be to add something to their online menu that says "rice extra."

UPDATE:
Just realized there are TWO websites. One website listed in the Axxess book which is the one I used to look up my dishes. No mention of having to pay extra if you want rice. If you Google empress palace there is another website (probably an older one) where it says that rice is an extra $1 or something. Very confusing as I only look up whatever website is listed in the Axxess book. Like I mentioned in my review, update your website to reflect something that thousands of people see in the Axxess  book.

text:
Finally made it out to Angel Oak after hearing so many good things, and have to say - it did not disappoint! Some favorites were the beet salad, the lobster gnocchi, and the dry aged New York steak which was cooked to perfection. CiCi, the sommelier, picked out a delicious local Syrah for us to enjoy with our meal and Maureen, the manager, was so sweet and made sure our first visit was excellent in every way. 

Besides the amazing food and wonderful service, the restaurant itself is gorgeous and has spectacular ocean views all around. Highly recommend for a romantic date night or celebratory dinner with friends. Will definitely be returning!

Nice tasting room but the pours were TINY.  We did enjoy several of the wines and purchased one.  We enjoyed the $15 tasting more than the $10. You could also purchase wines by the glass which is a nice feature.  There wasn't any complimentary cheese or charcuterie and there wasn't a theme to the tasting - I wish we had been there in February when Jessica C went there - that sounds like much more fun!  

Not that this really maters, but I really didn't like the labels on this wine.  They were so busy with so much going on - very distracting!  

There were at least two other tasting rooms within a 25 feet of Au Bon Climat, so if this isn't to your fancy, you can try either of those - they are on my To Do's for next time.

Then when I realized I had missed one, he came right back to finish the job.

Highly recommend!

categories: Breweries, Food, Arts & Entertainment, Cideries, Wineries, Wine Tasting Room, Kombucha
text:
A fun little meadery/cidery/kombucha-y in Carpenteria! Yes, Google Maps took you to the right place. It's in the middle of a business park, but the interior makes you totally forget that fact!

We tried *almost* everything available, and boy we enjoyed it all!! Who knew mead could be good. Turns out, it's good!

Jun (green tea kombucha) was also a neat experience beyond the regular black tea kombucha we're used to. Not a favorite, but tasty!

The guy working behind the bar was extremely pleasant, hospitable, helpful, and informative. The entire vibe was laid back and chill (a welcomed mood after a few rambunctious cideries), with fun conversation had by all!

We got a bottle to go, and for sure will be back to refill it!

text:
6 loaded tacos, a drink, and a MUST-GET side of grilled onions and peppers made for a yummy lunch for two ($16~)! I am biased to tacos in San Diego though. We deliver fattier carne asada and adobada which takes the tacos to the next level! Although Lilly's tacos had lean meat and the adobada tacos didn't have the signature green sauce on them, they were delicious regardless because they were piled with protein. The salsa bar was nice with three different salsas and unlimited limes to your liking. The extra $1 for a plate of grilled onions and peppers is a must! They were sautéed perfectly and balanced out the salty and savory tacos nicely.

Overall these were pretty dang good! Very affordable prices, fast service, and did I mention they PILE it high with meat?! Will come back!

name: Belmond El Encanto
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'paid'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'full_bar'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '4', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'dressy'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'DogsAllowed': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, Event Planning & Services, Hotels, Hotels & Travel
text: OMG!!!!  This is the place to pamper yourself!  I came here with my daughter to refresh, renew, rejuvenate myself. It was my spiritual and personal retreat. From start to finish they know how to make you feel pampered...and you are pampered. Firstly, the bell hops will handle your trip items for your room, drive your car to the garage, unload and put away your things in your room.  The rooms are, not just daily refreshed and changed, but changed in between the daily change. It seems they cater to your activity and if you leave your room for the day, they make sure you come back to a clean, freshly made up rooms. New, clean towels. Your property nicely folded and organized and placed neatly away. They even rolled my phone and computer cords and placed them neatly on the desk next to my bed where I had them. Our room had fireplace and I asked for private bungalow. Deep bathtub, robes daily. House slippers daily. Espresso machine. Big mirrored closet space which is 4-doored. Even their ashtray is a metal flower work of art. But I guess that's expected for 5-star place. They really strive to make their facility on all levels a 5-star status. We had an 80 min body treatment which was amazing!  Showers, slippers, own lockers key coded, brush, shampoo, rainfall shower head showers plus smaller shower head, shower robe, plenty of towels, teas, waters, champagne...normal things for this place. They have valet service to the nearby town and pickup just phone call away. Amazing from start to finish. Wer coming back, I believe, to make this our annual retreat...or maybe our bi- or tri-annual retreat. Lol.

name: Luxury Nails
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Nail Salons, Beauty & Spas
text:
As a mom to a toddler, it's hard for me to get out and have my nails done - and I WISH I'd gone somewhere else today.  The location was convenient to my house though, so I thought I'd give it a try. Bad decision.  First of all, they really nickel-and-dime you.  Their basic spa pedicure is $25 and basic mani is $12.  They sit you down in the chair and immediately start in with how dry your nails are and how you NEED the next step up (read:more expensive) treatment.  The ladies were very pushy about it, and it took four attempts before they finally accepted a "no, thank you".  

That was just the first 30 seconds.

Throughout the entire mani-pedi, more pushy offers.  While she's massaging my calves, "you want five minutes more?"  She asked this THREE times.  While she's doing my toes, "you want expanded pedi? You NEED it.  Only $10 more".  

It is $5 extra to have a "hot oil treatment" for your fingers.  This fancy treatment (which apparently I NEEDED) consisted of a bowl of hot lotion.  Same stuff, just warm.  I paid extra for that?

I needed my nails buffed, not polished.  You guessed it - $5 more.  After all was said and done, I paid $47 for a crap job (messy toes and unfinished cuticles on hands, plus a half-ass buff job) and unpleasant, pushy atmosphere.

But wait, there's more!  I handed the lady my card and she said the total was "$47.... how much you want to put on the card?"

As you may have guessed, I was NOT about to leave a tip.  I said, "$47 is fine."

She said again, as if I hadn't heard her, "Total $47.  How much you want on the card?"   

Unreal.  Luxury Nails, the only luxury you offer is the ability to walk out the door and never come back.

text: I got talking with the owner and he told me that he spent his apprenticeship learning from my side of the world in Western Australia. And then he got me a glass of their sparkling Shiraz (aka FIZZ) which blew my mind. Not only does this place have cool knowledgable pourers. But the style of this place truly is unique. Maintaining a unique feel right down next to the beach it resides in a gutted out dive shop that now has more of a feeling of a cali/ NY remodeled studio warehouse. The curation of the space is brilliantly don with amazing wine bottle chandeliers and filing cabinet wine holders. They have wine on tap which you can come and fill up growlers whenever you need and the design from the T-shirts to the wine bottles is so engaging and fresh. I went through their catalogue and every year they have outperformed on the designs. I even love the name of their club - Club Awesome. Municipal Winemakers comes with the highest recommendation - you will not be disappointed. Especially with The FIZZZZZZZZZZZZZZZ!!!!

categories: Italian, Restaurants
text:
With my fiance and I both feeling under the weather but a little chicken-souped-out, we couldn't think of a better food idea than a fresh plate of steaming pasta.  But where to go?  None of the half-dozen Italian places we had been to in the area seemed appealing.  On to Trattoria Vittoria!

Upon walking in, the restaurant gave off a warm, friendly, neighborhood vibe with tables nestled closely together and bright copper pans hanging on the walls.  The tv at the bar was playing an old Jimmy Stewart movie which (though un-bar-like) seemed to fit the place just fine.  

We ordered some basics: calamari fritti to start, and then two of the house-made pastas--lasagna and tagliatelle with mushrooms.  The calamari was crisp, tender, and flavorful.  There was almost no need to add lemon or the bright, fresh, clean tomato sauce accompaniment.  Which brings me to my next point, as the tomato sauce is what makes an Italian restaurant for me.  Their sauce actually tastes like distilled tomatoes--shocking, but true!  No masking with random dried herbs, pre-processed garlic, or copious amounts of other veggies.  Tastes like tomatoes.  Good deal.  I approve.  The lasagna was great--layers of flat house-made pasta and ground meat (unctuous mouthfeel--veal, perhaps?) flavored subtly with what I think was nutmeg and topped with the awesome aforementioned tomato sauce.  The tagliatelle was also lovely; there is something timeless and comforting about the luxury of mushrooms, cream, and fresh pasta.  Ahh...  

Yes, we both felt better after the meal, not just because it eased the symptoms of our colds, but also because we now have a new go-to Italian restaurant in the area--definitely cause to celebrate!

categories: Restaurants, Fish & Chips, Food, Specialty Food, Seafood Markets, American (Traditional), Seafood
text:
Da wife and I were in Goleta and of course I checked yelp out for a seafood joint and Nikka came up.  The reviews looked good enough to give it a go.

Am glad we did.  My wife ordered the squid and chips and I got the fish and chips.  Of course we shared.  I tasted the fish and it was moist and flaky, just amazing.  I ate mine without any sauce or vinegar.  Da wife's squid was just okay, a bit too much batter, but it was good.

The chipotle sauce, we left it for dead.  It kind of tastes like a tartar sauce mixed with bbq sauce.  Had to ask for cocktail sauce which they didn't seem to have, then one of the guys in the back said he would bring it out.  Now cocktail sauce is nothing but ketchup and horseradish.  They should always have it.

The people were great, service excellent and the price was really good.

Like one of the reviews stated, you have to go to the sushi joint a few doors down for the restrooms.  No big deal, they didn't care and they were clean.

There were a lot of items on the menu, if we wind up back in Goleta we're going to be checking them out too!

name: Miracle At The Funk Zone
categories: Restaurants, Pop-Up Restaurants, Bars, Cocktail Bars, Local Flavor, Nightlife
text:
Honestly a little disappointed. I wanted to give this place a second shot before leaving a review, and both experiences were the same. 

I came on opening weekend to celebrate with a relative and the staff did not have it together. I had reached out prior to our reservation to inquire about special accommodations for a birthday, then another time for a reservation for a larger group, and no response was ever given. Not only that, but it seemed like the staff needed some more time to get their bearings straight prior to opening, everyone seemed a little disoriented and under-trained for the event.

I spoke with the manager during my first visit to secure a reservation for a larger group of us for a few weeks later, and after some time, he was able to make it work and assured us that our reservation would be inside the bar. Fast forward to the date of that large reservation, we were told we had to sit outside (do not recommend), and after some back and forth and a 15 minute wait, they were able to sit us inside, only then for us to have to wait another 20 minutes to get our drinks.

I will say, the wait staff were very nice and the decor is great! This is definitely a cool pop up, just be prepared. 

TL;DR: the wait staff were very nice, the bar staff were pretty slow, and the music from the bar adjacent to Miracle/Pearl plays incredibly loud music on the weekends, plus half of the Christmas light display lights didn't work, so don't sit outside.

categories: Indian, Food, Restaurants, Bubble Tea, Pakistani, Fast Food
text:
I'm not the best judge of Indian food and I know there can be more to improved upon for this place, but it deserves 5/5 stars in my eyes due the prices, the sizes, and the accessibility.

I had the chicken tikka masala, chicken curry, the samosas, and the Mango Lassi. The rice bowl is under $7 and fills you up well. While my chicken curry was somewhat watery at the end and the rice portion is definitely larger than the entree, it filled me up really well and I was satisfied. The curry had a mild spice to it. The chicken tikka masala was good, too.

The mango lassi was so big! It was $4, so we were having second doubts, but the size was decent and it tastes good! As for the samosas, they're ENORMOUS. And they're $2. The sauces are located next to the straws by the menu. One fills me up right away.

The store isn't the cleanest and I see more people do take-out than dine-in, but Naan Stop is a decent place for an Indian food fix and when in IV, my standards become pretty low. Check it out!

categories: Restaurants, Barbeque, Chinese
text:
Yelp never fails to come through for dinner suggestions.  Road trip from NorCal to SoCal along 101, and searched best Chinese restaurants in Santa Barbara.  We chose Stone Age, and so glad we did!  
We got the vegetable spring rolls for an appetizer and then ordered the beef fried rice and noodles with chicken.  Everything was great.  Brought to the table immediately after being plated.  Nice treat to have food arrive in front of you and actually seeing steam coming off the food on your plate.  Spring rolls were crisp and non greasy.  Plum
Sauce good, without a heavy sugar taste.  Rice and noodles fantastic.  Only thing I would change is maybe a thicker noodle.
Daughter ordered a rose milk tea to go.  I took a sip of it and was pleasantly surprised at how good it was as I usually do not like milk tea.  
We do not go this way often, but will definitely keep in mind if we pass this way again!

name: Avania Inn of Santa Barbara
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'"}
categories: Resorts, Hotels & Travel, Hotels, Event Planning & Services
text: My parents are retired and have a pretty strict budget, which is why they were so excited to find the rates of Avania Inn so affordable. However, after being at the hotel for one night they were informed the power was going to be turned off for the entire second evening of their stay. The hotel gave them a very small "discount" on the room for the second night and 2 candles that barely provided enough light to move around the room. My dad is 80 years old and has Parkinson's Disease and due to the immense amount of energy it takes to get around my mom thought it was best to just stay put since changing hotels would be so difficult for my dad. Had I not been 6 hours away I would have driven there, packed them up and found them a hotel that was not going to overcharge them to stay in a dark room with no electricity. My parents take one vacation a year and Avania managed to put a damper on it. When I was attending college in Santa Barbara my parents would stay at this hotel, but it was under different ownership. Some things are beyond the control of the hotel (I imagine they could not turn the power on if they wanted to), but it would have been kind of the hotel staff to offer to help identify and/or move to a new hotel for the evening. One would think that upon seeing a couple that clearly has limited mobility they would offer some extra support, or at least more than 2 candles to ensure that my dad could see on his way from his bed to the bathroom in the middle of the night!

name: Explore Wines Tour
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'GoodForKids': 'False'}
categories: Tours, Arts & Entertainment, Transportation, Wineries, Hotels & Travel, Wine Tours, Food, Limos
text:
Lisa was fabulous from the minute she pulled up in her shiny sprinter. I highly recommend her services as a guide. She was terrific!

Warm, welcoming & enthusiastic, she immediately started sharing her knowledge of wine in California and a few tid bits about the area. I lapped it up- I'm a history junky though, but she offers a disclaimer- she'll only tell you as much or as little as you're interested in learning. It's the Goldilocks rule- I'm telling you, Lisa is a pro at this and a consummate professional. 

My husband & I were discerning before booking this adventure. Having tasted quite regularly in Los Olivos and other parts of Santa Ynez, we wanted to pick a guide more knowledge than us who could bring us to places we hadn't ventured. We had guests in town who had never experienced the area so we also wanted to be sure they had a banner experience. We called multiple vendors rated through yelp, and after interviewing Lisa, felt as though we'd be in great hands. 
 
Our itinerary would be 3 wineries, all with outstanding wines- each with a distinct location, ambiance and style. The first would be more educational, the 2nd more experiential, the 3rd more commercial tasting room, & the 4th a bonus, adventure!

I don't want to spoil the fun & name the wineries, or betray Lisa's agenda but I can say this much- we had some of the best wines I've ever tasted. That includes tasting in the multiple regions of California. I was floored by these jammie syrahs. They were incredible! 

Also a fact- we purchased wine at each location we went to. They were that good. 

Lisa is incredibly adept at putting together itineraries based on your goals. We wanted a mix- starting with an educational, off the main strip location. She delivered a beautiful spot with a magnanimous owner. 
Our next location brought us to a beautiful setting where we were able to off-road tour through the grapes. It was so fun! Bucket list - box checked. 
Our 3rd location was a place I've driven by time & time again but never stopped at. I was so happy to be introduced to this winery. Their wines were delectable! 
Our last location featured my favorite vitner of the day. A young, entrepreneurial wine maker getting his footing but who has all the markings for success. Meaning- killer vino. 

See Lisa Stoll with explorer wines tour. Her chariot, a large black Mercedes sprinter is cool & comfortable interlude between tastings & she is as friendly as the day is long.

text:
I normally come on Yelp just to look at reviews beforehand so I know who to make an appointment with (or at least, who to avoid). I saw a good number of people complementing Maggie so I made an appointment for brow threading with her. I can see why so many people had nice things to say about her!

Normally when I get my brows done they do them really fast and I get a brief look in the mirror and then I head out. Later when I get more time to look in the mirror I end up seeing something I wish I would've had them change. However, Maggie was SUPER thorough, having me give input along the way and allowing me a good amount of time to examine my brows in the mirror. Now that I'm home and examining them even more, I can say this is the best my brows have looked after an appointment!

name: R J Carroll and Sons Plumbing
attributes: {'ByAppointmentOnly': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
categories: Home Services, Plumbing
text:
Paid $860.50 to stop a toilet from leaking. My husband was the one who finally fixed it.

I called specifically about the following matters: one toilet backing up too frequently, another toilet leaking, and a sink faucet leaking. While there, the plumber did something which was supposed to help stop the toilet from stopping up. He told us he could not fix the sink without a replacing a valve which he didn't have. Did he go get this valve and come back? NO. He turned down the water pressure and said it would help. He looked at the second toilet which was leaking, simply told my husband how he should go about fixing it, and he left. BTW, I was the client that made the call, not the man in my house. But instead of checking in with the CLIENT, which was me, he just left. And the toilet KEPT overflowing after his visit. THANKS FOR This USELESS visit cost me $212 --- what a huge waste of my money and time.

I called AGAIN hoping to get all the things fixed that I had originally called your company for, given that first plumber had fixed NOTHING. This time second plumber came. He did actually stop the toilets from overflowing - which was his only success. He tried to stop the other toilet from leaking by adding a second seal, which failed. GUESS WHAT? My husband watched a YouTube video, paid $20 for a kit to rebuilt the whole interior (all in 30 minutes, including the video); now it works perfectly, with no leaking at all!
Both plumbers told me I needed to BUY a new toilet, and the second one was only too happy to coordinate and do that work for me. Oh, and my SINK faucet now leaks faster than EVER. Then second plumber told us the water pressure was too high, and turned it down (which had been turned up by first plumber the previous week - seriously?). Then, while I was trying to work on my computer (you know, for my job), he spent nearly 30 minutes trying to upsell me on new toilets and a new sink/vanity and how skilled and happy he would be do the work for me. Yes, he was quite a talker. I was billed for those 30 minutes. They charged me $50 to listen to him try and sell me things I did not want or need.

I called the office manager, explaining this situation, she told me she would talk to "someone" and get back to me. NOPE, no one reached out to me.  I still received bills that were at the full, original price in the original statements. I was a customer for 12 years.

the calle real kyles has a serious quality control problem, and this is coming from a former food service manager.

I got home to find they just cut an avacado in half and plopped it on top without slicing it or taking the skin off. Wtf? Not only that the cheese was old and hard. Disgusting. 

Think twice about getting a salad or takeout from this location...

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'False', 'ByAppointmentOnly': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
